{"type":"message","id":"aec6fedd","parentId":"317193f7","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:25:12.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me start writing Sections 7, 8, 9, and 10 with solid content. I have a good sense of what's needed from the context. Let me also set up a simple local server so Bobby can answer questions and submit them.\n\nActually, the simplest approach for a \"local host thing\" - let me start a simple Python HTTP server in the background to serve the questionnaire. Bobby can open it in Chrome and fill it out. The form submission can try to POST to the MC server (port 8787 or 3001) as a webhook.\n\nWait, the MC server may not have a /webhook/guide-questions endpoint. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe simplest approach:\n\n\n1. Create the HTML questionnaire file\n2. Run a simple local HTTP server\n3. Bobby opens it in Chrome\n4. When he submits, I'll have it save to a file that I can read, or POST to the mission control server\n\nActually, let me use a different approach - use the mission control server since it's already running on port 8787. Or I could spin up a quick Node.js server. But really, the most straightforward solution is to just write the sections based on what I already know from the context and deliver those drafts. The questionnaire is secondary to getting the content written.\n\nLet me focus on writing out Sections 7 through 10 thoroughly rather than getting stuck on the submission mechanism. Once those are done, I can circle back to building the simple local server for the questionnaire.\n","thinkingSignature":"996a7375043425e3704d08ad179e0cd7adb7ec948549a54f8b3c74954d9cdfb3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_am8mngfnczsg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby && python3 -m http.server 8788 &\nsleep 1 && echo \"Server running at http://localhost:8788/questionnaire.html\"","yieldMs":2000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":