{"type":"message","id":"371dbbfd","parentId":"db0ef98a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:29:23.258Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the current state of the file to see what's there now.\n","thinkingSignature":"757082f054e4b2f80bd228f0c357fc124825168682c989e334b0cee174c99151"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xgh2dgtfj3ap_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":742,"output":54,"cacheRead":69952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70748,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777652958768,"responseId":"064407dff855a03cda5988802652e0da"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5e33eb25","parentId":"371dbbfd","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:29:23.387Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xgh2dgtfj3ap_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n### Email (Gmail)\n\n- Access: Gmail API (not IMAP)\n- Config: ~/.config/gmail_creds.py\n- Uses OAuth2 refresh token for authentication\n\n### Calendar\n\n- Default: **Family Calendar** (iCloud, shared with Logan)\n- Other calendars: Home Calendar, Family Calendar, Birthdays, US Holidays\n\n### Browser\n\n- **USE CHROME** - it's the default for all browser automation\n- When Bobby sends a link, open it with browser tool: `browser action=open url=[link]`\n- web_fetch often fails for X/Twitter - use Chrome browser instead\n- **For X/Twitter posts:** Read ONLY the main post, not replies - unless Bobby specifies otherwise\n- When Bobby sends an X link, use that post/thread as context for what he is asking about before assuming he wants a new generated X section or unrelated output\n\n### Local Models (Ollama)\n\n- **Keep ChatGPT as main orchestrator** for complex planning, high-stakes reasoning, and long conversations\n- Prefer **local-main** (`ollama/qwen3.5:2b`) for lightweight recurring tasks, summaries, classification, and simple drafting\n- Prefer **local-tiny** (`ollama/qwen3.5:0.8b`) for ultra-light formatting/extraction tasks when possible\n- Prefer **local-code** (`ollama/qwen2.5-coder:3b`) for small coding, scripts, regex, and config edits\n- Prefer **local-fallback** (`ollama/llama3.2:3b`) if another local model behaves oddly\n- On this 8GB MacBook Air, avoid moving heavy reasoning or large agentic workflows fully local\n\n### Apple Music\n\n- Default playlist: **MY PLAYLIST**\n- Sometimes Bobby will ask to add songs to it\n\n### Morning Brief\n\n- **Skill:** ~/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md\n- Scheduled: 5:30 AM daily (via cron)\n- Includes: Weather (Knoxville), Bible verse, News (HN), Calendar (7 days), Reminders, Suggestions\n- Twitter tabs to open:\n  - For You: https://x.com/home (click \"For you\" tab after load)\n  - Following: https://x.com/home (click \"Following\" tab after load)\n  - Trending: https://x.com/explore\n\n### Mission Control Server\n- **Status:** Permanent LaunchAgent services (auto-start on boot, auto-restart on crash)\n- **Main server:** `com.bobby.mission-control` → port 8787\n- **Calendar API:** `com.bobby.mission-control-calendar` → port 3001\n- **URL:** http://127.0.0.1:8787\n- **Start:** `launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bobby.mission-control.plist`\n- **Stop:** `launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bobby.mission-control.plist`\n- **Logs:** ~/.openclaw/logs/mission-control.log\n\n### Morning Brief X Content Preferences\n\n- **Politics** - include political posts from feed\n- **OpenClaw** - tips on getting more out of OpenClaw\n- **Making Money** - tips on how to make money with agents/AI\n- Scroll through and curate actual good content, not just first posts\n\n---\n\n### Bill Tracker\n\n- **File:** `~/Desktop/bills_tracker.md`\n- Updated after each payment cycle\n\n---\n\n### 🚨 CRITICAL\n\n- **NEVER uninstall or stop the OpenClaw gateway service** — this is the core of everything\n- Keep the gateway running at all times\n- It should auto-start on boot\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n\n### Apple Music - Adding Songs\nWhen Bobby says \"queue next\" or \"play next\" → ADD TO \"MY PLAYLIST\" (don't play immediately). Play the current song, queue the new one to play after via the playlist.\nWhen Bobby says \"add this song\" or \"add to playlist\":\n1. Get currently playing: `osascript -e 'tell application \"Music\" to set cTrack to current track; return (name of cTrack & \" - \" & artist of cTrack)'`\n2. Add to MY PLAYLIST:\n```applescript\ntell application \"Music\"\n    set searchResults to search library playlist 1 for \"[song name]\"\n    set firstResult to item 1 of searchResults\n    duplicate firstResult to playlist \"MY PLAYLIST\"\nend tell\n```\nOr simpler - duplicate current track directly:\n```applescript\ntell application \"Music\"\n    duplicate (current track) to playlist \"MY PLAYLIST\"\nend tell\n```\n\n### Image Analyzer\n- **Skill:** ~/.openclaw/skills/image-analyzer/SKILL.md\n- **When Bobby sends an image:** Use `tesseract` (OCR) to analyze it since standard image tool fails\n- **How to analyze images:**\n  1. First try: `tesseract <image_path> stdout 2>/dev/null`\n  2. If that fails, use sharp to convert + tesseract:\n  ```bash\n  node -e \"const sharp=require('/tmp/node_modules/sharp'); sharp('<path>').resize(800,null,{withoutEnlargement:true}).jpeg({quality:80}).toFile('/tmp/img_small.jpg').then(()=>console.log('Done'))\"\n  tesseract /tmp/img_small.jpg stdout 2>/dev/null\n  ```\n- Tesseract installed at `/opt/homebrew/bin/tesseract` (v5.5.2)\n- Sharp available at `/tmp/node_modules/sharp`\n\n### Message Formatting Rules (Telegram)\n- **ALL links must be clickable:** Use `[text](url)` markdown format, NEVER plain URLs\n  - ✅ Correct: `[Fill out the questionnaire](http://localhost:8790/questionnaire.html)`\n  - ❌ Wrong: `http://localhost:8790/questionnaire.html` or `here's the link: http://...`\n- This applies to EVERY link — local URLs, web links, everything\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777652963386}}
