{"type":"message","id":"3a571e41","parentId":"e474c9cb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:39:45.837Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby sent 3 queued messages. Let me respond to all 3:\n\n1. He's confirming the clickable link worked with the 192.168.1.162:8790 format, and asking me to always send links that way\n2. Asking what the questionnaire is for - does it help complete the guide?\n3. Asking why I keep saying \"NO_REPLY\" or \"No follow-up needed\"\n\nFor #1 - the issue is that the localhost link doesn't work on his phone since the server is running on his Mac. The 192.168.1.162:8790 format works because it uses his LAN IP. I need to always use the LAN IP format when sending links to him via Telegram.\n\n\nFor #2 - the questionnaire helps me understand his preferences for the guide so I can write content tailored to what he wants.\nFor #3 - the NO_REPLY marker tells OpenClaw not to send a Telegram message, but since I'm already using the message tool directly to send to Telegram, that marker is unnecessary and causing confusion.\n\nI need to clarify two things with Bobby: the links need to use his LAN IP address instead of localhost since he's on his phone, and I should stop using NO_REPLY since I'm already handling Telegram delivery through the message tool directly.","thinkingSignature":"789b0eac778c231ad794d221785f20cb9d32c1b85de9dbb8c450d4a9707288e9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nUnderstood. From now on all links go as clickable Telegram messages sent directly, using your LAN IP format:\n\n[http://192.168.1.162:8790/questionnaire.html](http://192.168.1.162:8790/questionnaire.html)\n\n---\n\n**On the questionnaire:** Yes — it's how I fill in the gaps. The guide has shells for Sections 7, 8, 9 with no real content. Instead of guessing what you want, the form asks the key questions so I write it the way you intend. Title, tone, what goes in/out, your author bio, the conclusion — all of that shapes the final PDF. Answering it 