{"type":"message","id":"ac15d855","parentId":"62f689cb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:40:57.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking for title suggestions for his OpenClaw guide. He's selling it for $9 as a PDF, it's aimed at beginners starting from step 0, and it's the practical real-world guide he's been working on. Let me think of good titles that are clear, beginner-friendly, and convey the \"step by step from zero\" aspect.\n\nSome ideas:\n1. \"The OpenClaw Guide: From Zero to Running Your First AI Agent\"\n2. \"OpenClaw for Beginners: Build Your First Automation in 30 Minutes\"\n3. \"The Beginner's Guide to OpenClaw: Set It Up Once, Let It Run Forever\"\n4. \"OpenClaw Made Simple: A No-Fluff Guide for Beginners\"\n\n\n5. \"Your First OpenClaw: A Step-by-Step Guide for Beginners\"\n6. \"OpenClaw From Scratch: The Only Guide Beginners Need\"\n7. \"OpenClaw for People Who Don't Code: A Beginner's Practical Guide\"\n\nI should give Bobby a solid list of options and let him pick what feels right.\n","thinkingSignature":"13e58998fbec6a9460e14f2a0889231d90cf593418fe25d5a4d2d7280a932b7a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHere are some strong options:\n\n1. **\"The OpenClaw Guide for Beginners: From Zero to Your First Running Agent\"**\n2. **\"OpenClaw Start to Finish: The No-Fluff Beginner's Guide\"**\n3. **\"OpenClaw for People Who Don't Code: A Step-by-Step Guide for Beginners\"**\n4. **\"Build Your First OpenClaw Automation: The Beginner's Guide\"**\n5. **\"OpenClaw Made Simple: From Setup to Your First Automation in 30 Minutes\"**\n6. **\"The Only OpenClaw Guide Beginners Need: Start Here, Go All the Way\"**\n7. **\"OpenClaw: Zero to Running — A Practical Guide for Beginners\"**\n\nMy top pick for your audience:\n> **\"OpenClaw for Beginners: Your First Automation, Start to Finish\"**\n\nSimple, honest, sets the right expectation. Someone scrolling a $9 product page knows exactly what they're getting.\n\nWant me to run a few by Rex for SEO/comparison with what's selling on Gumroad, or are these enough to pick from?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74843,"output":444,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75607,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777653630842,"responseId":"06440a7f044c1aa06ba5374c273ea03a"}}
