{"type":"message","id":"f77c61de","parentId":"73c375b8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T16:57:17.488Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby sent a voice memo saying there's nothing to listen to and I should be using the system voice with no specific voice specified. Let me try using the whisper CLI to transcribe it first, then respond appropriately.\n\nActually, re-reading: \"there is nothing to listen to here\" - he might be saying MY voice memo has nothing to listen to? Or he's testing my response?\n\nWait - the inbound context shows my previous message had `<media:audio>` and he replied to it saying \"there is nothing to listen to here.\" \n\nSo my voice memo didn't work properly. He received it but there's nothing to listen to (the audio is empty or broken). And he's saying I should be using the system voice (no specific -v flag).\n\nLet me check the audio file and also try to send a proper voice memo using the system voice with just `say` (no -v flag, which uses the default system voice).\n","thinkingSignature":"15956c8812e7f88b885837613a6a6dc2997f2fd51844bf3f1b55ed67c1473ac1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zmo0x3a45417_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"say \"Hey Bobby, from now on I'll send voice memos using your system voice. No extra flags, just talking to you straight. Quick and easy replies coming your way.\" -o /tmp/dean_v2.m4a && echo \"done\"","yieldMs":8000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":78516,"output":273,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79109,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777654616262,"responseId":"06440e58800dd86072cf96ec777c8986"}}
