{"type":"message","id":"b7f51c61","parentId":"3e6d5cee","timestamp":"2026-05-01T17:02:56.839Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking if I read his texts. He's referring to the queued messages from earlier that came through after the gateway restart. Let me check what messages came through.\n\nLooking at the queued messages earlier:\n1. \"thank you. this is what i mean that i eed the clickable link\" - about the clickable link format\n2. \"and what exactly is this questionaire for like does this help you compelete and finish the openclaw guide?\" - asking about the questionnaire\n3. \"why do you keep sending No follow-up needed from me.\" - asking about NO_REPLY\n\nThen my response covered all three of those. And then there was the discussion about voice memos and the title picking.\n\n\nI did respond to those queued messages about the clickable link format, the questionnaire's purpose, and the NO_REPLY behavior. Then we moved into discussing voice memo format and picking a title for the guide, which is where we left off.\n","thinkingSignature":"64d7fb2b1f2cb8058afe1a985e27092c90c239f9eaa0d5bd75d9c54adde4f4a5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes — I got all of them:\n\n1. ✅ Clickable link — we fixed it (using the LAN IP format going forward)\n2. ✅ Questionnaire explained — it's how I fill in Sections 7, 8, 9 to finish the guide\n3. ✅ NO_REPLY explained — just prevents duplicate messages, nothing to worry about\n\nThen we did the voice memo setup and talked about titles. Rex's pick was **\"The OpenClaw Playbook\"** as the title. Still waiting on your number pick.\n\nWhere are you at on the questionnaire? Running into any issues with it or ready to fill it out?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80715,"output":325,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81232,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestam