{"type":"message","id":"89f6ec7b","parentId":"133619f4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:38:43.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both are running. Now let me test if the microphone access works. But the issue is that the microphone request (getUserMedia) needs to be triggered by a user gesture in Safari. Since Bobby is clicking the mic button, that should work. But Safari might be blocking it.\n\nLet me check if there's an issue with the server.js first by testing the multipart parsing. Actually, the main issue Bobby had was that Safari wasn't even requesting mic permission. With the new code that uses navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia, Safari should ask for permission when he clicks the mic button.\n\nLet me verify the servers are working and inform Bobby it should be ready now.","thinkingSignature":"280bf7ed1f95830628216f66f825c562b9d4ba5105fbd75952cfcad5ca0dc530"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nBoth servers are running. Try the updated page — tap the mic button and Safari should ask for microphone permission.\n\n[http://localhost:8790/telephone.html](http://localhost:8790/telephone.html)\n\nIf you still get \"Mic access denied\" it means Safari is blocking the mic. Let me know what it says."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":267,"output":204,"cacheRead":107840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108311,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777664319913,"responseId":"0644344075a12cddf4ac1b2d88d2da87"}}
