{"type":"message","id":"40688c48","parentId":"bafe58e5","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:40:05.208Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby called me out - I violated the clickable link rule. I just sent a plain URL in text. The correct thing to do was to send it as a proper Telegram message (which I did - the message tool sends it as a proper clickable link). But I also included it in my chat reply as plain text.\n\nActually wait - looking at this more carefully, I sent the plain URL text in my response above (not via the message tool), but I also sent a proper message via the message tool. So Bobby got the clickable link via Telegram, but my chat reply had the plain URL.\n\nLet me be more careful. In the chat reply itself, I should use proper markdown link format. The message tool already sends clickable links natively in Telegram. Let me update my reply here to use the proper format.\n","thinkingSignature":"cad991e9c45c6c23eb86d16453cf089f1fb4f35b2069398bdb3d79d1ebc7cd30"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n[http://localhost:8790/telephone.html](http://localhost:8790/telephone.html)\n\nSorry — I keep failing on this. Sending it via Telegram message automatically makes it clickable there. In text replies I'm now using `[text](url)` format. Adding it to my rules too so I don't slip up again."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":158,"output":239,"cacheRead":108160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777664394598,"responseId":"0644348a7a834964785bdffa61cfe91e"}}
