{"type":"message","id":"32b40556","parentId":"2ff1eb92","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:49:12.985Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The TailScale URL works and Telegram recognizes it as a URL entity. But the issue is that localhost:8790 is not going to work from Bobby's iPhone - that's his Mac's localhost.\n\nWait - the issue is that Bobby can't click the links because:\n1. `http://localhost:...` URLs - these are localhost on HIS iPhone, not on the Mac, so they won't work\n2. The plain text URL `http://localhost:8790/telephone.html` - Telegram might not auto-linkify it\n\nThe TailScale URL `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html` DID get recognized as a URL with `entities`.\n \nSo the solution is to always use the TailScale URL instead of localhost when sending links to Telegram. The problem was that I was sending localhost links to Bobby's phone, which of course won't resolve there - I needed to use the publicly accessible TailScale address that Bobby can actually reach from his iPhone.\n","thinkingSignature":"eacc218b6153e8312409b570c2451561af90988ce05545b122c5a176583eb2bb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g464k4qj7b8b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"open https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":389,"output":256,"cacheRead":74816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75461,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777664947357,"responseId":"064436b3b7d5b608e756428b1deda21a"}}
