{"type":"message","id":"82aa84b0","parentId":"1c6c02bc","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:12:08.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The inline keyboard was successfully sent via direct API call. Let me figure out how to get the `message` tool to use this format.\n\nLet me look at how the presentation/buttons format works in the message tool. I was using:\n```\npresentation: {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"Open Telephone\", \"style\": \"primary\", \"url\": \"https://...\"}]}]}\n```\n\nBut maybe the Telegram plugin expects a different structure. Let me check if the plugin uses `reply_markup` differently.\n\nActually, the problem might be that when I use `presentation` with `blocks`, the Telegram plugin might not be converting it to `reply_markup` correctly. \n\nI need to examine how the plugin actually processes these blocks and whether it's properly serializing the inline keyboard markup for Telegram.\n","thinkingSignature":"6b0bf10d51b4f1d24267304d05eba2773f2a0568bcdb09f9f181715e1ac19304"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xznj7xpfzeab_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw -name \"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"inline_keyboard\\|reply_markup\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":141,"output":238,"cacheRead":62848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63227,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666323302,"responseId":"06443c132158bc869e999e940176c3ee"}}
