{"type":"message","id":"98b33497","parentId":"64612637","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:12:36.873Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the `buildInlineKeyboard` function is in the Telegram extension. The `presentation.blocks` format I was using should work, but maybe it's not being passed correctly. Let me look at how `blocks` maps to `buttons`.\n\nThe issue might be that `presentation.blocks[0].buttons` has objects with `url` and `label`, but the `buildInlineKeyboard` function expects a specific format. Let me check what format the buttons need to be in.\n\nActually, from what I can see:\n- `buildInlineKeyboard(buttons)` takes buttons directly\n- The buttons format should be `[{text, url}]`\n\nSo when I pass:\n```json\n{\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"Open Telephone\", \"url\": \"https://...\", \"style\": \"primary\"}], \"type\": \"buttons\"}]}\n\n\n```\n\nThe extension should extract `blocks[0].buttons` and convert `label` → `text`. But clearly something's going wrong because Bobby isn't seeing the button. Let me try sending a reply markup directly through the Telegram API to see if that works, then I can debug the OpenClaw presentation format from there.\n\nBobby's screenshot confirms it: the \"No follow-up needed from me\" text is coming from the system, not from my message tool. So I need to stop relying on that parameter and figure out how to properly format the inline keyboard buttons so they actually appear.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"340880bd0b9b6d038b764274af55d6ea1e6fee4e3c640d893591875e0c1e0a5a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hodsq8iyhqs0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A30 \"function buildInlineKeyboard\" /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/telegram/send-bzTgoQhn.js 2>/dev/null | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":383,"output":364,"cacheRead":64192,"cacheWrite"