{"type":"message","id":"7626b0bd","parentId":"b540862f","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:13:40.117Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTML text_link format works via curl. But the question is - when OpenClaw's message tool sends with `presentation: {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [...]}]}`, what format does it actually send?\n\nLooking at the `buildInlineKeyboard` function - it only supports `callback_data` buttons, NOT URL buttons! The buttons it builds are for callback queries, not for opening URLs.\n\nSo the `presentation.blocks[].buttons[].url` approach is WRONG for this Telegram implementation. It probably doesn't support URL buttons at all through that path.\n\nThe correct approach for clickable links in Telegram is HTML `<a href=\"url\">text</a>` with `parse_mode=HTML`. But the message tool doesn't expose this - it uses the `presentation` format which maps to callback_data buttons.\n\n\nI should just send it via curl directly using HTML format instead of trying to work around the message tool's limitations.\n","thinkingSignature":"d212c38e9d64bc0309d45475e375b2ca2fe709033b8c6f49dc7a002027fddb1f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_myp3l9kte0cg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['channels']['telegram']['accounts']['default']['botToken'])\")\n\ncurl -s \"https://api.telegram.org/bot${TOKEN}/sendMessage\" \\\n  -d 'chat_id=8212808444&text=Tap to open Telephone:\n👉 <a href=\"https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html\">Open Telephone</a>&parse_mode=HTML' 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('sent:', d['ok'])\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":340,"output":366,"cacheRead":65792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66498,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stop