{"type":"message","id":"3a2717ab","parentId":"10725c2b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:20:33.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Whisper works fine on clean audio. The issue is that the audio being recorded from the browser through MediaRecorder and sent as multipart/webm is not being transcribed properly. The \"Could not transcribe\" is the fallback when whisper returns empty text.\n\nThe problem is likely:\n1. The webm audio from Safari MediaRecorder might have a different format\n2. The multipart parsing in server.js might be writing corrupted audio files\n3. The webm file might not be a proper audio format\n\nLet me check by actually testing with a real webm file. But I can't do that from the browser. Let me look at what could go wrong.\n\nActually, looking at the server.js multipart parsing more carefully:\n\n\nThe binary string conversion corrupts binary data, and splitting on `\\r\\n\\r\\n` boundaries might fail if the browser sends a different format than expected. The transcription itself is failing - whisper is either not getting a proper audio file or the webm format isn't supported. Looking at the logs, Bobby's message consistently comes back empty, which suggests the audio file itself is the issue, not the conversation history.\n","thinkingSignature":"3853e127531b0b7e99be2f4d77186bc350fb7b4bc4cbd766a4260f31f6a8b779"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_01cc1cz4cusn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Clean up old messages and restart the services\npkill -f \"dean.js\" 2>/dev/null; pkill -f \"server.js\" 2>/dev/null\nsleep 1\n\n# Restart\ncd ~/Desktop/Telephone && node server.js > ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone.log 2>&1 &\nsleep 1\nnode dean.js > ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-dean.log 2>&1 &\nsleep 2\n\nps aux | grep -E \"server\\.js|dean\\.js\" | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":168,"output":368,"cacheRead":80128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalT