{"type":"message","id":"d3c7dd0b","parentId":"f54e13b2","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:22:44.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now:\n\n1. **\"Could not transcribe\"** — Whisper keeps failing to transcribe Bobby's audio. This is the core problem. Every time Bobby speaks, the transcription fails.\n\n2. **Shell syntax error with emoji** — The 🤖🦞 emoji in the prompt are breaking the curl command. But even with the error, Dean is still generating \"I'm here Bobby, what's up?\" somehow.\n\n3. **No conversation context** — Bobby wants Dean to know things about him and have actual conversations, not just say \"what's up?\"\n\nThe root problem is: **Safari's microphone recording isn't working correctly for Whisper transcription**. \n\nLet me trace through the flow:\n1. Bobby holds mic button → MediaRecorder starts capturing audio\n\n\n2. Bobby releases → MediaRecorder stops and sends chunks via fetch POST to /talk\n3. Server receives audio blob and writes it to disk as .webm\n4. FFmpeg converts .webm to .mp3\n5. Whisper transcribes the .mp3 → \"Could not transcribe\"\n6. Because transcription fails, Dean falls back to default greeting\n\nThe problem is the audio file itself—either Whisper can't process the Safari MediaRecorder format, or the transcription is silently failing and returning empty. I should test what Whisper outputs when it fails versus succeeds.\n\nI'm also noticing a bug: the browser sends chunks to the server every second, so the POST completes and returns before the full audio is recorded. This means the audio blob is incomplete. The fix is to not stop the recording when the button is released, but instead wait for the audio to finish uploading, then manually stop the recording after the fetch completes.\n\nLooking at the code more carefully, I see there's a race condition: `stopListening()` sets `isRecording = false` and calls `mediaRecorder.stop()`, but the `onstop` event fires asynchronously. Since `audioChunks` is being populated during recording, stopping the MediaRecorder before the final chunks are collected means the incomplete audio gets sent to the server. The event loop continues after `stopListening()` returns, so the `onstop` handler fires and sends whatever chunks have been accumulated so far.\n\nThe `transcribeAudio` function uses `execSync` to run whisper and save results to a text file. If whisper fails or produces empty output, the callback receives a fallback message. I need to trace through what happens when the transcription actually succeeds versus when it doesn't.\n\nThe real problem is that Bobby's speech isn't being transcribed at all—whisper returns \"Could not transcribe\" or the result is empty. This could mean whisper is failing silently, or the audio file itself isn't being captured properly. The MediaRecorder might not be receiving audio because the mic permission wasn't granted. I should rebuild this with a simpler approach that handles the audio capture and transcription pipeline more robustly.\n\nI'm considering using the system `asr` tool for speech recognition, but it requires trained audio files which won't work here. A Node.js speech-to-text library like `node-record-lpcm16` could be an alternative to Safari's MediaRecorder, though it requires a separate installation. The most practical solution is to test the actual audio files being created and figure out whether the issue is with microphone access or the transcription step itself.\n\nLet me check if whisper is actually receiving audio or if it's failing silently. I think the real problem might be that the audio blob isn't being sent completely—`mediaRecorder.stop()` fires before all chunks are gathered, so the fetch completes with an incomplete file. I should wait for the `onstop` event to fire and ensure all chunks are collected before sending. Alternatively, I could switch to a Node.js-based recording solution instead of relying on the browser's MediaRecorder API.","thinkingSignature":"01585c2b4d403b68654dd0f9b9edaf19c5f2b8e94651ef9919172f92a29858b6"},{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear now:\n\n1. **Safari audio isn't being transcribed** — Whisper says \"Could not transcribe\" every time\n2. **The curl command with emoji is broken** — shell syntax error prevents proper AI calls\n\nLet me rebuild this properly. The whole architecture is fragile. I'll simplify it.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x7t9w56mjc8t_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Telephone — Dean Response Generator\n * Watches for new user messages, generates responses, posts audio back\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync, spawn } = require('child_process');\n\nconst SERVER = 'http://localhost:8791';\nconst PORT_DEAN = 8791;\nconst PORT_GATEWAY = 8787;\nconst STATE_FILE = path.join(__dirname, '.last_check');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'messages.json');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'audio');\nconst WHISPER_MODEL = 'small';\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\n// Load last check time\nlet lastCheck = 0;\nif (fs.existsSync(STATE_FILE)) {\n  try { lastCheck = parseInt(fs.readFileSync(STATE_FILE, 'utf8')) || 0; } catch(e) {}\n}\n\nfunction saveLastCheck(ts) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(STATE_FILE, String(ts));\n}\n\nfunction getNewMessages() {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const url = `http://localhost:${PORT_DEAN}/messages?since=${lastCheck}`;\n    http.get(url, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n      res.on('end', () => {\n        try {\n          const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n          resolve(parsed.messages || []);\n        } catch(e) { resolve([]); }\n      });\n    }).on('error', () => resolve([]));\n  });\n}\n\nfunction postReply(text) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const postData = JSON.stringify({ text, fromDean: true });\n    const req = http.request({\n      hostname: 'localhost',\n      port: PORT_DEAN,\n      path: '/reply',\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData) }\n    }, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', c => data += c);\n      res.on('end', () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch(e) { resolve({ ok: false }); } });\n    });\n    req.on('error', () => resolve({ ok: false }));\n    req.write(postData);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    // Strip problematic characters for say command\n    const clean = text\n      .replace(/[\"\\\\'‘’\"\"«»]/g, '')\n      .replace(/[🤖🦞🔥💀😂❤️👍✨📺🎉💡]/g, '')\n      .replace(/\\n+/g, ' ')\n      .replace(/\\s+/g, ' ')\n      .trim();\n    \n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o \"${aiffPath}\"`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i \"${aiffPath}\" \"${mp3Path}\" -y`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    \n    try { fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath); } catch(e) {}\n    \n    callback(mp3Path);\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('[Telephone] TTS error:', e.message);\n    callback(null);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction callAI(userText, conversationHistory, callback) {\n  // Build conversation context\n  let context = '';\n  if (conversationHistory.length > 0) {\n    const recent = conversationHistory.slice(-6);\n    context = recent.map(m => `${m.from === 'dean' ? 'Dean' : 'Bobby'}: ${m.text}`).join('\\n') + '\\n';\n  }\n\n  const systemPrompt = `You are Dean, Bobby's main AI assistant on the Telephone app. Keep responses SHORT — 1 to 2 sentences max. Casual, conversational, like talking to a friend who you've known for years. Never repeat the same greeting. Be warm, helpful, and direct. Bobby is speaking to you through a voice app.`;\n\n  const userContent = context \n    ? `Recent conversation:\\n${context}\\nBobby: ${userText}\\nDean:`\n    : `Bobby: ${userText}\\nDean:`;\n\n  const body = JSON.stringify({\n    model: 'minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7',\n    messages: [\n      { role: 'system', content: systemPrompt },\n      { role: 'user', content: userContent }\n    ],\n    max_tokens: 150,\n    temperature: 0.8\n  });\n\n  const url = new URL(`http://localhost:${PORT_GATEWAY}/v1/chat/completions`);\n  const options = {\n    hostname: url.hostname,\n    port: url.port || 8787,\n    path: url.pathname,\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(body)\n    }\n  };\n\n  const req = http.request(options, (res) => {\n    let data = '';\n    res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n    res.on('end', () => {\n      try {\n        const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n        const reply = parsed.choices?.[0]?.message?.content?.trim();\n        if (reply) {\n          callback(reply);\n        } else {\n          console.error('[Telephone] AI response empty:', data.substring(0, 200));\n          callback(\"I'm here Bobby, say something!\");\n        }\n      } catch(e) {\n        console.error('[Telephone] AI parse error:', e.message, data.substring(0, 200));\n        callback(\"I'm here Bobby, say something!\");\n      }\n    });\n  });\n\n  req.on('error', (e) => {\n    console.error('[Telephone] AI connection error:', e.message);\n    callback(\"I'm here Bobby, say something!\");\n  });\n\n  req.write(body);\n  req.end();\n}\n\nasync function processLoop() {\n  try {\n    const messages = await getNewMessages();\n    \n    for (const msg of messages) {\n      if (msg.from === 'user' && msg.text && !msg.text.includes('Could not transcribe') && !msg.text.includes('Transcription failed')) {\n        console.log(`[Telephone] Bobby said: ${msg.text}`);\n        \n        // Get full message history for context\n        let history = [];\n        try {\n          const data = fs.readFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, 'utf8');\n          history = JSON.parse(data);\n        } catch(e) {}\n        \n        // Remove this message from history we're about to process (we'll re-save after)\n        history = history.filter(m => m.timestamp !== msg.timestamp);\n        \n        saveLastCheck(msg.timestamp);\n        \n        // Call AI with the user's text and history\n        callAI(msg.text, history, async (reply) => {\n          console.log(`[Telephone] Dean says: ${reply}`);\n          \n          // Generate audio\n          textToAudio(reply, async (mp3Path) => {\n            if (mp3Path) {\n              await postReply(reply);\n              console.log(`[Telephone] Audio reply posted: ${mp3Path}`);\n            }\n          });\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('[Telephone] Process error:', e.message);\n  }\n  \n  setTimeout(processLoop, 3000);\n}\n\n// Start\nconsole.log('[Telephone] Dean started — watching for messages');\nprocessLoop();\n","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51557,"output":2523,"cacheRead":32885,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666924490,"responseId":"06443e6c2d58b08b978b65a18d25eb81"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f81adc0c","parentId":"d3c7dd0b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:22:44.789Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x7t9w56mjc8t_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 6348 bytes to /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666964789}}
{"type":"message","id":"c507a02a","parentId":"f81adc0c","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:23:05.390Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also fix the server.js to handle the audio transcription properly. The issue with \"Could not transcribe\" might be that:\n1. The audio file is empty or in a format whisper can't read\n2. The multipart parsing is wrong\n3. The ffmpeg conversion is failing\n\nLet me rewrite the server.js to be more robust about handling audio transcription, and add better error logging so we can see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"afed5f2950980914133d1ef7c0a36607330d8b6d0af00e54a1022e49881e8745"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me also fix the server to properly handle audio transcription:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_og7k97venxgp_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\n\nconst PORT = 8791;\nconst DIR = __dirname;\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(DIR, 'audio');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(DIR, 'messages.json');\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\nfunction saveMessages(msgs) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, JSON.stringify(msgs, null, 2));\n}\n\nfunction loadMessages() {\n  if (fs.existsSync(MESSAGES_FILE)) {\n    try { return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(MESSAGES_FILE, 'utf8')); } catch(e) {}\n  }\n  return [];\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    const clean = text\n      .replace(/[\"\\\\'‘’\"\"«»]/g, '')\n      .replace(/[🤖🦞🔥💀😂❤️👍✨📺🎉💡]/g, '')\n      .replace(/\\n+/g, ' ')\n      .replace(/\\s+/g, ' ')\n      .trim();\n    \n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o \"${aiffPath}\"`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i \"${aiffPath}\" \"${mp3Path}\" -y`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    try { fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath); } catch(e) {}\n    callback(mp3Path);\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('TTS error:', e.message);\n    callback(null);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction transcribeAudio(audioPath, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = `/tmp/telephone_rec_${ts}.mp3`;\n  const txtPath = `/tmp/telephone_rec_${ts}.txt`;\n  \n  try {\n    // Convert to mp3 with specific settings for whisper\n    const ffmpegResult = execSync(\n      `ffmpeg -i \"${audioPath}\" -ac 1 -ar 16000 -c:a pcm_s16le \"${mp3Path}\" -y 2>&1`,\n      { stdio: 'pipe' }\n    );\n    \n    // Check if file was created\n    if (!fs.existsSync(mp3Path)) {\n      console.error('[Transcribe] MP3 file not created');\n      callback('Could not transcribe');\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    const stats = fs.statSync(mp3Path);\n    if (stats.size < 1000) {\n      console.error('[Transcribe] MP3 file too small:', stats.size);\n      callback('Could not transcribe');\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    // Run whisper\n    execSync(\n      `whisper \"${mp3Path}\" --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp --verbose False 2>/dev/null`,\n      { stdio: 'pipe' }\n    );\n    \n    const text = fs.existsSync(txtPath) ? fs.readFileSync(txtPath, 'utf8').trim() : '';\n    \n    // Cleanup\n    try { fs.unlinkSync(mp3Path); } catch(e) {}\n    try { fs.unlinkSync(txtPath); } catch(e) {}\n    \n    if (text && text.length > 0) {\n      callback(text);\n    } else {\n      callback('Could not transcribe');\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('[Transcribe] Error:', e.message);\n    try { fs.unlinkSync(mp3Path); } catch(e) {}\n    callback('Could not transcribe');\n  }\n}\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, X-Since');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(200);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve audio files\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/audio/')) {\n    const filename = path.basename(req.url);\n    const filePath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, filename);\n    if (fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'audio/mpeg' });\n      fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n    } else {\n      res.writeHead(404);\n      res.end('Not found');\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Receive audio from browser\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/talk') {\n    const chunks = [];\n    req.on('data', c => chunks.push(c));\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      const buffer = Buffer.concat(chunks);\n      const contentType = req.headers['content-type'] || '';\n      const boundary = contentType.match(/boundary=(.+)/)?.[1];\n\n      if (!boundary) {\n        // Plain JSON\n        try {\n          const { text } = JSON.parse(buffer.toString());\n          const messages = loadMessages();\n          messages.push({ from: 'user', text, timestamp: Date.now() });\n          saveMessages(messages);\n          res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ received: true, transcript: text }));\n          return;\n        } catch(e) {\n          res.writeHead(400);\n          res.end('Bad request');\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Parse multipart\n      const parts = buffer.toString('binary').split('--' + boundary).filter(p => p.includes('Content-Disposition'));\n\n      for (const part of parts) {\n        if (part.includes('name=\"audio\"')) {\n          const fileMatch = part.match(/Content-Type:\\s*audio\\/([\\w]+)/);\n          const ext = fileMatch ? fileMatch[1] : 'webm';\n          const audioPath = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `recording_${Date.now()}.${ext}`);\n          \n          // Extract binary data after double CRLF\n          const parts_data = part.split('\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n          if (parts_data.length < 2) continue;\n          \n          const binaryData = parts_data.slice(1).join('\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n          fs.writeFileSync(audioPath, Buffer.from(binaryData, 'binary'));\n\n          // Check file size\n          const stats = fs.statSync(audioPath);\n          console.log(`[Server] Received audio: ${stats.size} bytes, ext: ${ext}`);\n\n          transcribeAudio(audioPath, (text) => {\n            console.log(`[Server] Transcription: \"${text}\"`);\n            const messages = loadMessages();\n            messages.push({ from: 'user', text, timestamp: Date.now() });\n            saveMessages(messages);\n\n            // Cleanup\n            try { fs.unlinkSync(audioPath); } catch(e) {}\n\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ received: true, transcript: text }));\n          });\n\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n\n      res.writeHead(400);\n      res.end('No audio found');\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Get new messages\n  if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url.startsWith('/messages')) {\n    const since = parseInt(req.headers['x-since'] || '0');\n    const messages = loadMessages();\n    const newOnes = messages.filter(m => m.timestamp > since);\n    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    res.end(JSON.stringify({ messages: newOnes }));\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Dean posts reply\n  if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/reply') {\n    let body = '';\n    req.on('data', c => body += c);\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      try {\n        const { text, fromDean } = JSON.parse(body);\n        if (fromDean) {\n          textToAudio(text, (mp3Path) => {\n            if (mp3Path) {\n              const messages = loadMessages();\n              messages.push({\n                from: 'dean',\n                text,\n                audioFile: `/audio/${path.basename(mp3Path)}`,\n                timestamp: Date.now()\n              });\n              saveMessages(messages);\n            }\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }));\n          });\n        } else {\n          res.writeHead(200);\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }));\n        }\n      } catch(e) {\n        res.writeHead(400);\n        res.end('Bad request');\n      }\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  res.writeHead(404);\n  res.end('Not found');\n});\n\nserver.listen(PORT, () => {\n  console.log(`Telephone server running on port ${PORT}`);\n});\n","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/server.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54117,"output":2112,"cacheRead":32885,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89114,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777666964796,"responseId":"06443e946d65d1803b60901ac0ead074"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5673f806","parentId":"c507a02a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:23:05.536Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_og7k97venxgp_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 7497 bytes to /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/server.js"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777666985535}}
{"type":"message","id":"b17329e2","parentId":"5673f806","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:23:33.972Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also fix the telephone.html to handle the recording more reliably. The issue with the browser recording might be that the MediaRecorder isn't capturing complete audio. Let me rewrite the frontend to be simpler and more robust.","thinkingSignature":"5ef8a879c6e6d68bce63309b7c6b4c7656755b204f76827a28781efd62753d28"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me fix the frontend to handle the mic recording properly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w1c6fzq7leu0_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Telephone — Dean</title>\n  <style>\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    body {\n      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n      background: #0a0a0f;\n      color: #e0e0e0;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      overflow: hidden;\n      user-select: none;\n    }\n\n    #fairy-canvas {\n      position: fixed;\n      top: 0; left: 0;\n      width: 100%; height: 100%;\n      z-index: 0;\n      pointer-events: none;\n    }\n\n    .ui {\n      position: relative;\n      z-index: 1;\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      gap: 24px;\n    }\n\n    .status {\n      font-size: 14px;\n      color: #666;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      min-height: 20px;\n    }\n\n    .status.listening { color: #ff6b6b; }\n    .status.thinking { color: #ffd93d; }\n    .status.replying { color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .mic-btn {\n      width: 100px;\n      height: 100px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 3px solid #333;\n      background: #1a1a24;\n      cursor: pointer;\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      transition: all 0.2s;\n      position: relative;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn:hover { border-color: #555; background: #222; }\n    .mic-btn.on { border-color: #ff6b6b; background: #2a1a1a; box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.3); }\n\n    .mic-btn svg {\n      width: 36px;\n      height: 36px;\n      fill: #888;\n      transition: fill 0.2s;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on svg { fill: #ff6b6b; }\n\n    .pulse-ring {\n      position: absolute;\n      width: 100%;\n      height: 100%;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 2px solid #ff6b6b;\n      opacity: 0;\n      animation: none;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on .pulse-ring { animation: pulse 1.5s ease-out infinite; }\n\n    @keyframes pulse {\n      0% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 0.8; }\n      100% { transform: scale(1.8); opacity: 0; }\n    }\n\n    .transcript {\n      font-size: 13px;\n      color: #555;\n      max-width: 400px;\n      text-align: center;\n      min-height: 40px;\n      padding: 0 20px;\n    }\n\n    .transcript.visible { color: #aaa; }\n\n    .hint {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #444;\n      position: fixed;\n      bottom: 30px;\n    }\n\n    .reply-indicator {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #3a3a3a;\n      position: fixed;\n      bottom: 50px;\n      opacity: 0;\n      transition: opacity 0.3s;\n    }\n\n    .reply-indicator.show { opacity: 1; color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .error-msg {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #ff6b6b;\n      max-width: 300px;\n      text-align: center;\n      padding: 0 20px;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<canvas id=\"fairy-canvas\"></canvas>\n\n<div class=\"ui\">\n  <div class=\"status\" id=\"status\">Tap to talk</div>\n  <button class=\"mic-btn\" id=\"mic-btn\">\n    <div class=\"pulse-ring\"></div>\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M12 14c1.66 0 3-1.34 3-3V5c0-1.66-1.34-3-3-3S9 3.34 9 5v6c0 1.66 1.34 3 3 3zm5.91-3c-.49 0-.9.36-.98.85C16.52 14.2 14.47 16 12 16s-4.52-1.8-4.93-4.15c-.08-.49-.49-.85-.98-.85-.61 0-1.09.54-1 1.14.49 3 2.89 5.35 5.91 5.78V20c0 .55.45 1 1 1s1-.45 1-1v-2.08c3.02-.43 5.42-2.78 5.91-5.78.1-.6-.39-1.14-1-1.14z\"/></svg>\n  </button>\n  <div class=\"transcript\" id=\"transcript\"></div>\n  <div class=\"error-msg\" id=\"error-msg\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reply-indicator\" id=\"reply-indicator\">Dean is replying...</div>\n<div class=\"hint\">Hold mic to record, release to send</div>\n\n<script>\n// === Fairy Light System ===\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('fairy-canvas');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nlet lights = [];\nlet currentMode = 'idle';\n\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\n  canvas.width = window.innerWidth;\n  canvas.height = window.innerHeight;\n}\nresizeCanvas();\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\n\nconst NUM_LIGHTS = 60;\nfor (let i = 0; i < NUM_LIGHTS; i++) {\n  lights.push({\n    x: Math.random() * canvas.width,\n    y: Math.random() * canvas.height,\n    vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.5,\n    vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.5,\n    size: Math.random() * 3 + 1,\n    brightness: Math.random() * 0.5 + 0.3,\n    hue: Math.random() * 60 + 20,\n    twinkle: Math.random() * Math.PI * 2,\n    twinkleSpeed: Math.random() * 0.05 + 0.02\n  });\n}\n\nfunction drawLight(l, intensity) {\n  const alpha = l.brightness * intensity;\n  ctx.save();\n  ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;\n  ctx.fillStyle = `hsl(${l.hue}, 80%, 70%)`;\n  ctx.shadowBlur = 15 * intensity;\n  ctx.shadowColor = `hsl(${l.hue}, 90%, 60%)`;\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  ctx.arc(l.x, l.y, l.size * (0.8 + intensity * 0.4), 0, Math.PI * 2);\n  ctx.fill();\n  ctx.restore();\n}\n\nfunction updateLights() {\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    l.x += l.vx;\n    l.y += l.vy;\n    l.twinkle += l.twinkleSpeed;\n    if (l.x < 0 || l.x > canvas.width) l.vx *= -1;\n    if (l.y < 0 || l.y > canvas.height) l.vy *= -1;\n    l.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;\n    l.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;\n    l.vx = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, l.vx));\n    l.vy = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, l.vy));\n  }\n}\n\nfunction getIntensity() {\n  if (currentMode === 'listening') return 1.8;\n  if (currentMode === 'replying') return 2.0;\n  if (currentMode === 'thinking') return 0.4 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.005) * 0.4;\n  return 0.8 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.001) * 0.15;\n}\n\nfunction animate() {\n  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n  updateLights();\n  const intensity = getIntensity();\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    const tw = 0.7 + Math.sin(l.twinkle) * 0.3;\n    drawLight(l, intensity * tw);\n  }\n  requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n}\nanimate();\n\n// === Mic Recording ===\nconst micBtn = document.getElementById('mic-btn');\nconst status = document.getElementById('status');\nconst transcript = document.getElementById('transcript');\nconst replyIndicator = document.getElementById('reply-indicator');\nconst errorMsg = document.getElementById('error-msg');\n\nlet mediaRecorder = null;\nlet audioChunks = [];\nlet isRecording = false;\nlet audioStream = null;\n\nfunction showError(msg) {\n  errorMsg.textContent = msg;\n  setTimeout(() => { errorMsg.textContent = ''; }, 5000);\n}\n\nasync function startListening() {\n  errorMsg.textContent = '';\n  transcript.textContent = '';\n  transcript.classList.remove('visible');\n\n  try {\n    audioStream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ \n      audio: {\n        echoCancellation: true,\n        noiseSuppression: true,\n        autoGainControl: true\n      }\n    });\n  } catch(e) {\n    showError('Mic access denied — check Safari permissions');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  isRecording = true;\n  currentMode = 'listening';\n  micBtn.classList.add('on');\n  status.textContent = 'Listening...';\n  status.className = 'status listening';\n\n  audioChunks = [];\n\n  // Prefer webm/opus, fallback to mp4\n  const mimeType = MediaRecorder.isTypeSupported('audio/webm;codecs=opus') \n    ? 'audio/webm;codecs=opus' \n    : MediaRecorder.isTypeSupported('audio/mp4') \n      ? 'audio/mp4' \n      : 'audio/webm';\n\n  mediaRecorder = new MediaRecorder(audioStream, { mimeType });\n\n  mediaRecorder.ondataavailable = (event) => {\n    if (event.data && event.data.size > 0) {\n      audioChunks.push(event.data);\n    }\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onstop = async () => {\n    if (audioChunks.length === 0) {\n      status.textContent = 'No audio recorded';\n      currentMode = 'idle';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const blob = new Blob(audioChunks, { type: mimeType });\n    const fileSize = blob.size;\n    console.log('[Telephone] Recording complete:', fileSize, 'bytes');\n    \n    await sendAudio(blob);\n    audioChunks = [];\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onerror = (e) => {\n    console.error('[Telephone] MediaRecorder error:', e);\n    showError('Recording error');\n    isRecording = false;\n    micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.start();\n  console.log('[Telephone] Recording started, mime:', mimeType);\n}\n\nfunction stopListening() {\n  if (!isRecording || !mediaRecorder) return;\n  isRecording = false;\n  micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n  status.textContent = 'Processing...';\n\n  if (mediaRecorder.state !== 'inactive') {\n    mediaRecorder.stop();\n  }\n\n  if (audioStream) {\n    audioStream.getTracks().forEach(t => t.stop());\n  }\n}\n\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mousedown', startListening);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); startListening(); });\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mouseup', stopListening);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mouseleave', stopListening);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); stopListening(); });\n\nasync function sendAudio(blob) {\n  try {\n    const formData = new FormData();\n    formData.append('audio', blob, 'recording.webm');\n\n    const resp = await fetch('http://localhost:8791/talk', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      body: formData\n    });\n\n    const data = await resp.json();\n    \n    if (data.transcript) {\n      transcript.textContent = data.transcript;\n      transcript.classList.add('visible');\n    }\n\n    if (data.received) {\n      pollForReply();\n    } else {\n      status.textContent = 'Error — tap to retry';\n      currentMode = 'idle';\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('[Telephone] Send error:', e);\n    status.textContent = 'Connection error';\n    currentMode = 'idle';\n  }\n}\n\nlet lastReplyCheck = 0;\nlet pollInterval = null;\n\nasync function pollForReply() {\n  status.textContent = 'Dean is thinking...';\n  status.className = 'status thinking';\n  currentMode = 'thinking';\n\n  const checkReply = async () => {\n    try {\n      const resp = await fetch('http://localhost:8791/messages?since=' + lastReplyCheck);\n      const data = await resp.json();\n\n      const deanMsg = data.messages?.find(m => m.from === 'dean');\n      if (deanMsg && deanMsg.audioFile) {\n        lastReplyCheck = deanMsg.timestamp;\n        currentMode = 'replying';\n        status.textContent = 'Dean';\n        status.className = 'status replying';\n        replyIndicator.classList.add('show');\n\n        const audio = new Audio('http://localhost:8791' + deanMsg.audioFile);\n        audio.play();\n\n        audio.onended = () => {\n          currentMode = 'idle';\n          status.textContent = 'Tap to talk';\n          status.className = 'status';\n          replyIndicator.classList.remove('show');\n        };\n\n        audio.onerror = () => {\n          currentMode = 'idle';\n          status.textContent = 'Tap to talk';\n          status.className = 'status';\n          replyIndicator.classList.remove('show');\n        };\n\n        return;\n      }\n\n      setTimeout(checkReply, 2000);\n    } catch(e) {\n      setTimeout(checkReply, 3000);\n    }\n  };\n\n  checkReply();\n}\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\n","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56265,"