{"type":"message","id":"cfe97b8b","parentId":"b0b1674e","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:25:37.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Whisper works fine on system audio. The issue is that when Safari records audio, it's using the web page's audio context which may not capture speech from the speaker properly. But wait — we're using `getUserMedia` to get the microphone. The issue is Safari on iPhone might be recording from the wrong audio source.\n\nWait, actually the real issue might be simpler. When Bobby speaks into the iPhone's microphone through Safari, Safari might not be getting any audio data because:\n\n1. iOS Safari has security restrictions — it needs explicit permission to use the microphone, and even then the audio context might be suspended until a user gesture.\n\n\n2. More fundamentally though, Safari on iOS doesn't support the Web Speech API at all, so there's no speech recognition capability to begin with. That's likely the core blocker here.\n\nLet me reconsider the transcription pipeline — the MediaRecorder approach should theoretically work since it bypasses the SpeechRecognition API entirely. But the whisper tool is reporting that the audio file is too small, which suggests either the recording isn't capturing any audio, the file isn't being sent to the server properly, or there's an issue with how ffmpeg is processing the data.\n\nLooking at the error message, ffmpeg is failing when trying to convert the webm file to mp3 format. Since ffmpeg needs audio input to process, this points to the webm file being corrupt or empty — likely because the MediaRecorder in Safari iOS isn't actually capturing audio from the microphone, even though permission was granted. I need to verify that `getUserMedia` is actually working on iOS Safari with the correct audio constraints.\n\nI could try a few approaches: simplifying the audio constraints, using the device's microphone ID if available, or switching to an AAC-encoded MediaRecorder format instead of webm. But first, let me test a manual recording to confirm whether iOS Safari can capture audio at all.\n","thinkingSignature":"73eccebfaac2ebf5595dba27d08a65d136b1858e4fd20d805de6a50c03ca9e55"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4199s5gonuju_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what audio formats iOS Safari supports for MediaRecorder\n# Also check if there's an issue with how the webm is being parsed\n\n# Let's test if the issue is the webm file itself\nls -la ~/Desktop/Telephone/audio/ | grep recording | tail -5\n# Try to probe the last recording with ffmpeg\nffmpeg -i ~/Desktop/Telephone/audio/recording_1777667060581.webm 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":194,"output":512,"cacheRead":92256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92962,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667132560,"responseId":"06443f3cc60e4efaf2f13d5a44eac0d9"}}
