{"type":"message","id":"243cc704","parentId":"5fd3b171","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:25:39.048Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xt44gq6wh1vh_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/audio/recording_1777667060581.webm: cannot open `/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/audio/recording_1777667060581.webm' (No such file or directory)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/audio/recording_1777667060581.webm: cannot open `/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/audio/recording_1777667060581.webm' (No such file or directory)","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777667139048}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfc12a33","parentId":"243cc704","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:25:42.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file was deleted already. The issue is clear from the logs - the webm file exists (76541 bytes) but ffmpeg fails to convert it. Let me check if ffmpeg supports webm/opus properly. Actually, looking at the error - it seems ffmpeg just failed to decode the webm. This could be because:\n1. The webm is using a codec ffmpeg doesn't support\n2. The file is corrupted\n3. The webm container format isn't what ffmpeg expects\n\nLet me check what webm audio codec Safari uses with MediaRecorder. Safari supports `audio/webm;codecs=opus` but ffmpeg might not have been built with libopus support properly, or the webm format from Safari uses some specific encoding that ffmpeg's built version can't handle.\n\n\nI should try forcing the conversion with explicit codec parameters or fall back to aac/m4a format that Safari might support better, since the current webm approach isn't working. The real issue is that the transcription keeps failing and reverting to a generic response, so I need to fix the audio pipeline itself - either by getting whisper to work properly with Safari's webm output or by switching to a format that avoids this problem entirely. Let me reconsider what Bobby actually needs here rather than continuing down this technical rabbit hole.","thinkingSignature":"3f0081cdf943512870dfd79235bed626db4e5ac7a5228d35dc64ce6bbc2e8671"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e3nvzcs57qjf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try converting with explicit format handling\nffmpeg -formats 2>/dev/null | grep -i webm\n# Test ffmpeg with a known good file\nffmpeg -i /tmp/test_speech.mp3 -ac 1 -ar 16000 /tmp/test_conv.mp3 -y 2>&1 | tail -3\nwhisper /tmp/test_conv.mp3 --model small --language English --output_format txt --output_dir /tmp 2>&1 | tail -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":193,"output":402,"cacheRead":92896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93491,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667139050,"responseId":"06443f43223771b0448fac6765721d71"}}
{"type":"message","id":"083462f8","parentId":"bfc12a33","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:25:52.026Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e3nvzcs57qjf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D   matroska,webm   Matroska / WebM\n  E  webm            WebM\n  E  webm_chunk      WebM Chunk Muxer\n DE  webm_dash_manifest WebM DASH Manifest\n[libmp3lame @ 0x9f7020a80] Trying to remove 576 samples, but the queue is empty\n[out#0/mp3 @ 0x9f6c68180] video:0KiB audio:8KiB subtitle:0KiB other streams:0KiB global headers:0KiB muxing overhead: 2.592593%\nsize=       9KiB time=00:00:02.77 bitrate=  25.6kbits/s speed= 295x elapsed=0:00:00.00    \n  warnings.warn(\"FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\")\n[00:00.000 --> 00:02.800]  Hello Bobby, this is a test of the transcription system."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9061,"aggregated":"D   matroska,webm   Matroska / WebM\n  E  webm            WebM\n  E  webm_chunk      WebM Chunk Muxer\n DE  webm_dash_manifest WebM DASH Manifest\n[libmp3lame @ 0x9f7020a80] Trying to remove 576 samples, but the queue is empty\n[out#0/mp3 @ 0x9f6c68180] video:0KiB audio:8KiB subtitle:0KiB other streams:0KiB global headers:0KiB muxing overhead: 2.592593%\nsize=       9KiB time=00:00:02.77 bitrate=  25.6kbits/s speed= 295x elapsed=0:00:00.00    \n  warnings.warn(\"FP16 is not supported on CPU; using FP32 instead\")\n[00:00.000 --> 00:02.800]  Hello Bobby, this is a test of the transcription system.","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777667152025}}
{"type":"message","id":"adf43103","parentId":"083462f8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:26:20.079Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The whisper transcription works fine on normal audio files. The problem is clearly that the audio files from Safari's MediaRecorder aren't being properly received by the server.\n\nLet me trace through the flow again:\n1. browser sends audio via FormData with \"audio\" field\n2. server parses multipart and saves as .webm\n3. server runs ffmpeg to convert to mp3\n4. server runs whisper on the mp3\n\nThe error in the logs said \"Command failed: ffmpeg -i ... -ac 1 -ar 16000 -c:a pcm_s16le ...\" - the ffmpeg command failed. But the file was already deleted by the time I checked.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The real issue might be that the multipart parsing is corrupting the binary audio data. When I do `Buffer.from(binaryData, 'binary')`, this might not work correctly for all binary data.\n\nA more robust approach would be to NOT use multipart parsing at all. Instead, have the browser send the audio as a raw ArrayBuffer and the server just reads it directly.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach:\n- Browser sends audio as `application/octet-stream` raw binary\n- Server reads the raw body and saves it as a file\n- No multipart parsing needed\n\nOr even simpler - send as base64 encoded JSON.\n\nActually, let me step back. The cleanest solution that will definitely work:\n\n1. Browser sends audio as base64 in JSON: `{\"audio\": \"...base64...\"}`\n2. Server decodes base64 and saves as webm\n3. Server runs ffmpeg → mp3 → whisper\n\nThis avoids ALL multipart parsing issues.\n\nLet me rewrite the server and frontend with this approach.","thinkingSignature":"f1f4ea82b64f5811fc697efd1dd3bc6850724336f68bffe4fc3298842d7bec7b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe issue is the multipart parsing is breaking the audio. Let me rewrite it to use base64 JSON instead — much more reliable.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6n7o7pdmwyeo_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Telephone — Dean</title>\n  <style>\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    body {\n      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n      background: #0a0a0f;\n      color: #e0e0e0;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      overflow: hidden;\n      user-select: none;\n    }\n\n    #fairy-canvas {\n      position: fixed;\n      top: 0; left: 0;\n      width: 100%; height: 100%;\n      z-index: 0;\n      pointer-events: none;\n    }\n\n    .ui {\n      position: relative;\n      z-index: 1;\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      gap: 24px;\n    }\n\n    .status {\n      font-size: 14px;\n      color: #666;\n      letter-spacing: 2px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n      min-height: 20px;\n    }\n\n    .status.listening { color: #ff6b6b; }\n    .status.thinking { color: #ffd93d; }\n    .status.replying { color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .mic-btn {\n      width: 100px;\n      height: 100px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 3px solid #333;\n      background: #1a1a24;\n      cursor: pointer;\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      transition: all 0.2s;\n      position: relative;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn:hover { border-color: #555; background: #222; }\n    .mic-btn.on { border-color: #ff6b6b; background: #2a1a1a; box-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.3); }\n\n    .mic-btn svg {\n      width: 36px;\n      height: 36px;\n      fill: #888;\n      transition: fill 0.2s;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on svg { fill: #ff6b6b; }\n\n    .pulse-ring {\n      position: absolute;\n      width: 100%;\n      height: 100%;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 2px solid #ff6b6b;\n      opacity: 0;\n      animation: none;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on .pulse-ring { animation: pulse 1.5s ease-out infinite; }\n\n    @keyframes pulse {\n      0% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 0.8; }\n      100% { transform: scale(1.8); opacity: 0; }\n    }\n\n    .transcript {\n      font-size: 13px;\n      color: #555;\n      max-width: 400px;\n      text-align: center;\n      min-height: 40px;\n      padding: 0 20px;\n    }\n\n    .transcript.visible { color: #aaa; }\n\n    .hint {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #444;\n      position: fixed;\n      bottom: 30px;\n    }\n\n    .reply-indicator {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #3a3a3a;\n      position: fixed;\n      bottom: 50px;\n      opacity: 0;\n      transition: opacity 0.3s;\n    }\n\n    .reply-indicator.show { opacity: 1; color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .error-msg {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #ff6b6b;\n      max-width: 300px;\n      text-align: center;\n      padding: 0 20px;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<canvas id=\"fairy-canvas\"></canvas>\n\n<div class=\"ui\">\n  <div class=\"status\" id=\"status\">Tap to talk</div>\n  <button class=\"mic-btn\" id=\"mic-btn\">\n    <div class=\"pulse-ring\"></div>\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M12 14c1.66 0 3-1.34 3-3V5c0-1.66-1.34-3-3-3S9 3.34 9 5v6c0 1.66 1.34 3 3 3zm5.91-3c-.49 0-.9.36-.98.85C16.52 14.2 14.47 16 12 16s-4.52-1.8-4.93-4.15c-.08-.49-.49-.85-.98-.85-.61 0-1.09.54-1 1.14.49 3 2.89 5.35 5.91 5.78V20c0 .55.45 1 1 1s1-.45 1-1v-2.08c3.02-.43 5.42-2.78 5.91-5.78.1-.6-.39-1.14-1-1.14z\"/></svg>\n  </button>\n  <div class=\"transcript\" id=\"transcript\"></div>\n  <div class=\"error-msg\" id=\"error-msg\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reply-indicator\" id=\"reply-indicator\">Dean is replying...</div>\n<div class=\"hint\">Hold mic to record, release to send</div>\n\n<script>\n// === Fairy Light System ===\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('fairy-canvas');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nlet lights = [];\nlet currentMode = 'idle';\n\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\n  canvas.width = window.innerWidth;\n  canvas.height = window.innerHeight;\n}\nresizeCanvas();\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\n\nconst NUM_LIGHTS = 60;\nfor (let i = 0; i < NUM_LIGHTS; i++) {\n  lights.push({\n    x: Math.random() * canvas.width,\n    y: Math.random() * canvas.height,\n    vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.5,\n    vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.5,\n    size: Math.random() * 3 + 1,\n    brightness: Math.random() * 0.5 + 0.3,\n    hue: Math.random() * 60 + 20,\n    twinkle: Math.random() * Math.PI * 2,\n    twinkleSpeed: Math.random() * 0.05 + 0.02\n  });\n}\n\nfunction drawLight(l, intensity) {\n  const alpha = l.brightness * intensity;\n  ctx.save();\n  ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;\n  ctx.fillStyle = `hsl(${l.hue}, 80%, 70%)`;\n  ctx.shadowBlur = 15 * intensity;\n  ctx.shadowColor = `hsl(${l.hue}, 90%, 60%)`;\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  ctx.arc(l.x, l.y, l.size * (0.8 + intensity * 0.4), 0, Math.PI * 2);\n  ctx.fill();\n  ctx.restore();\n}\n\nfunction updateLights() {\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    l.x += l.vx;\n    l.y += l.vy;\n    l.twinkle += l.twinkleSpeed;\n    if (l.x < 0 || l.x > canvas.width) l.vx *= -1;\n    if (l.y < 0 || l.y > canvas.height) l.vy *= -1;\n    l.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;\n    l.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;\n    l.vx = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, l.vx));\n    l.vy = Math.max(-1, Math.min(1, l.vy));\n  }\n}\n\nfunction getIntensity() {\n  if (currentMode === 'listening') return 1.8;\n  if (currentMode === 'replying') return 2.0;\n  if (currentMode === 'thinking') return 0.4 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.005) * 0.4;\n  return 0.8 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.001) * 0.15;\n}\n\nfunction animate() {\n  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n  updateLights();\n  const intensity = getIntensity();\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    const tw = 0.7 + Math.sin(l.twinkle) * 0.3;\n    drawLight(l, intensity * tw);\n  }\n  requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n}\nanimate();\n\n// === Mic Recording ===\nconst micBtn = document.getElementById('mic-btn');\nconst status = document.getElementById('status');\nconst transcript = document.getElementById('transcript');\nconst replyIndicator = document.getElementById('reply-indicator');\nconst errorMsg = document.getElementById('error-msg');\n\nlet mediaRecorder = null;\nlet audioChunks = [];\nlet isRecording = false;\nlet audioStream = null;\n\nfunction showError(msg) {\n  errorMsg.textContent = msg;\n  setTimeout(() => { errorMsg.textContent = ''; }, 5000);\n}\n\nasync function startListening() {\n  errorMsg.textContent = '';\n  transcript.textContent = '';\n  transcript.classList.remove('visible');\n\n  try {\n    audioStream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ \n      audio: {\n        echoCancellation: true,\n        noiseSuppression: true,\n        autoGainControl: true\n      }\n    });\n  } catch(e) {\n    showError('Mic access denied — check Safari permissions');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  isRecording = true;\n  currentMode = 'listening';\n  micBtn.classList.add('on');\n  status.textContent = 'Listening...';\n  status.className = 'status listening';\n  audioChunks = [];\n\n  const mimeType = MediaRecorder.isTypeSupported('audio/webm;codecs=opus') \n    ? 'audio/webm;codecs=opus' \n    : MediaRecorder.isTypeSupported('audio/mp4') \n      ? 'audio/mp4' \n      : 'audio/webm';\n\n  mediaRecorder = new MediaRecorder(audioStream, { mimeType });\n\n  mediaRecorder.ondataavailable = (event) => {\n    if (event.data && event.data.size > 0) {\n      audioChunks.push(event.data);\n    }\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onstop = async () => {\n    if (audioChunks.length === 0) {\n      status.textContent = 'No audio recorded';\n      currentMode = 'idle';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const blob = new Blob(audioChunks, { type: mimeType });\n    await sendAudio(blob);\n    audioChunks = [];\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onerror = (e) => {\n    showError('Recording error');\n    isRecording = false;\n    micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.start();\n}\n\nfunction stopListening() {\n  if (!isRecording || !mediaRecorder) return;\n  isRecording = false;\n  micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n  status.textContent = 'Processing...';\n\n  if (mediaRecorder.state !== 'inactive') {\n    mediaRecorder.stop();\n  }\n\n  if (audioStream) {\n    audioStream.getTracks().forEach(t => t.stop());\n  }\n}\n\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mousedown', startListening);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); startListening(); });\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mouseup', stopListening);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mouseleave', stopListening);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); stopListening(); });\n\nasync function sendAudio(blob) {\n  try {\n    // Convert blob to base64\n    const buffer = await blob.arrayBuffer();\n    const base64 = btoa(String.fromCharCode.apply(null, new Uint8Array(buffer)));\n    \n    const resp = await fetch('http://localhost:8791/talk', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ audio: base64, format: mimeType })\n    });\n\n    const data = await resp.json();\n    \n    if (data.transcript) {\n      transcript.textContent = data.transcript;\n      transcript.classList.add('visible');\n    }\n\n    if (data.received) {\n      pollForReply();\n    } else {\n      status.textContent = 'Error — tap to retry';\n      currentMode = 'idle';\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    status.textContent = 'Connection error';\n    currentMode = 'idle';\n  }\n}\n\nlet lastReplyCheck = 0;\n\nasync function pollForReply() {\n  status.textContent = 'Dean is thinking...';\n  status.className = 'status thinking';\n  currentMode = 'thinking';\n\n  const checkReply = async () => {\n    try {\n      const resp = await fetch('http://localhost:8791/messages?since=' + lastReplyCheck);\n      const data = await resp.json();\n\n      const deanMsg = data.messages?.find(m => m.from === 'dean');\n      if (deanMsg && deanMsg.audioFile) {\n        lastReplyCheck = deanMsg.timestamp;\n        currentMode = 'replying';\n        status.textContent = 'Dean';\n        status.className = 'status replying';\n        replyIndicator.classList.add('show');\n\n        const audio = new Audio('http://localhost:8791' + deanMsg.audioFile);\n        audio.play();\n\n        audio.onended = () => {\n          currentMode = 'idle';\n          status.textContent = 'Tap to talk';\n          status.className = 'status';\n          replyIndicator.classList.remove('show');\n        };\n\n        audio.onerror = () => {\n          currentMode = 'idle';\n          status.textContent = 'Tap to talk';\n          status.className = 'status';\n          replyIndicator.classList.remove('show');\n        };\n\n        return;\n      }\n\n      setTimeout(checkReply, 2000);\n    } catch(e) {\n      setTimeout(checkReply, 3000);\n    }\n  };\n\n  checkReply();\n}\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":396,"output":3606,"cacheRead":93056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97058,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667152034,"responseId":"06443f5055186c83a81fe269c2255c94"}}
