{"type":"message","id":"9f5269c4","parentId":"55ae2707","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:27:44.122Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mission-control-api.cjs is running on port 8787, not OpenClaw. So I need to use the OpenClaw gateway's actual port for the AI API. The OpenClaw gateway is on port 18789.\n\nLet me look at the OpenClaw gateway docs or config to find the correct path for chat completions.\n\nActually, thinking about this more practically - the OpenClaw gateway at port 18789 provides the web UI and the agent API. But the `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint might not exist or might be at a different path.\n\nLet me think about this differently. Instead of trying to fix the connection to OpenClaw gateway, let me use the OpenClaw API directly through the `sessions_send` tool or spawn a subagent. But that's not real-time enough for a telephone conversation.\n \nI could route through the Telegram bot instead - send the transcribed audio to Bobby there and let him respond through the bot. But that defeats the whole voice-first purpose of Telephone. The real goal here is voice-to-voice communication where Bobby speaks, I transcribe and respond with voice, all in under 30 seconds. To make that work, I need the OpenClaw API to handle the AI responses properly.\n\nLet me check what port and path the OpenClaw gateway actually exposes for chat completions.\n","thinkingSignature":"86e72f859f2fa0c35a73f9f5beaf52bc1cf0ff4c473017a79fada0ebdc402afa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c6gs03m4vzvh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\ngw = d.get('gateway', {})\nprint('port:', gw.get('port'))\nprint('mode:', gw.get('mode'))\nprint('bind:', gw.get('bind'))\nprint('keys:', list(gw.keys()))\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":345,"output":377,"cacheRead":102240,"cacheW