{"type":"message","id":"abe4de1e","parentId":"a1cf9931","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:28:01.057Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look for how the mission control server communicates with the OpenClaw gateway. The gateway was configured at port 18789 but maybe the mission control API is also on 8787. Let me check the TOOLS.md for the actual gateway port.\n\nActually, TOOLS.md says:\n```\n### Mission Control Server\n- **Status:** Permanent LaunchAgent services (auto-start on boot, auto-restart on crash)\n- **Main server:** `com.bobby.mission-control` → port 8787\n```\n\nSo the mission control is on 8787, not the OpenClaw gateway. And the OpenClaw gateway is on 18789. \n\nI've been trying to route through the mission control API at 8787 to reach the OpenClaw gateway, but that's not working either. Looking back at SOUL.md, it mentions the OpenClaw Gateway running on port 8787, which contradicts what I'm seeing in my tools configuration. I need to figure out where the gateway is actually running and how to properly connect to it.","thinkingSignature":"98cbfe1e9b64068746a4bc587b5946ee77f1f5362983f67016468c29597ac293"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nub96634exv5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"8787\\|gateway\\|port\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":87,"output":261,"cacheRead":103808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104156,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667278300,"responseId":"06443fced0132ad5f47c08644c440d4f"}}
