{"type":"message","id":"563fbffc","parentId":"442af60b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:28:35.139Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. The OpenAI-compatible HTTP API (`/v1/chat/completions`) is disabled by default. I need to enable it in the gateway config.\n\nBut wait - the mission-control server (port 8787) IS proxying to the gateway. Let me check the correct way to call it through the proxy. Maybe the path is different.\n\nActually, looking at the prod-server.cjs more carefully:\n```javascript\nif (pathname.startsWith('/tools/')) {\n  await proxyRequest(req, res, GATEWAY_PORT);\n```\n\nSo `/tools/` is the prefix for gateway proxying. Let me test:\n```\n\n\ncurl -X POST \"http://localhost:8787/tools/v1/chat/completions\"\n```\n\nBut first, let me check if the endpoint is enabled. I should look at the current gateway config to see whether `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions` is actually enabled or if it's disabled by default.","thinkingSignature":"ce8a2f2afbd47c1f8319d01446041bd1f649c294caea87d2a52df6670922c0ff"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vlkx5i6amjr9_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get","path":"gateway.http.endpoints"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":436,"output":235,"cacheRead":109696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110367,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667312721,"responseId":"06443ff0fbcb24ec7e19a85e3b876c93"}}
