{"type":"compaction","id":"ba992587","parentId":"c5ca5e17","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:29:37.116Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\n1. **Retry failed Morning Brief cron job** — Done, ran successfully\n2. **Finish The OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.** — $9 PDF, write/complete Sections 7-10, compile final PDF\n3. **Build \"Telephone\"** — Voice-first communication tool with fairy lights, system voice responses, local-only\n4. **Fix Telephone transcription** — Safari mic recording is not being transcribed by Whisper; Dean keeps saying \"I'm here Bobby, what's up?\"\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Guide: $9, PDF only, no audio, no sales page yet — priority is finishing the PDF content\n- **Telegram links must be sent as HTML `<a href=\"url\">text</a>` with `parse_mode=HTML`** — OpenClaw's `presentation.blocks[].buttons[].url` format does NOT work (buildInlineKeyboard only supports `callback_data` buttons, not URL buttons). Direct Telegram API with `reply_markup` inline keyboard with `url` fields also doesn't render as clickable buttons in the app.\n- All Telegram links must use Tailscale URL (`https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/...`) to be accessible from iPhone\n- Voice memos: system default voice (no `-v` flag), MP3 format via `say` + ffmpeg, sent via `message action=send asVoice=true`\n- When Bobby reports a problem, fix immediately and note it\n- Keep replies short, conversational, easy to answer back\n- Telephone must use: Safari, toggle mic, audio only, tap to replay, dark theme, fairy lights with 3 different formations for (speaking / thinking / replying)\n- Telephone: completely local, separate from the guide/questionnaire project\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Morning Brief retried and ran successfully\n- [x] Created `~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/questionnaire.html` for author questions\n- [x] Added clickable-link rule and voice memo format rules to `TOOLS.md`\n- [x] Consulted Rex for guide title\n- [x] Built Telephone: `telephone.html`, `server.js` (port 8791), `dean.js` background processor\n- [x] HTTP server on port 8790, Node server on port 8791, dean.js background process — all running\n- [x] Fixed Telegram link formatting — HTML `<a href>` with `parse_mode=HTML` works (creates blue underlined clickable text). Updated TOOLS.md with correct method.\n- [x] Rebuilt dean.js with HTTP request instead of shell curl (avoids emoji shell syntax errors) and conversation context/history\n- [x] Rebuilt server.js with better transcription error handling and file size checks\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Telephone: Whisper not transcribing** — Every audio recording returns \"Could not transcribe\". Dean responds with \"I'm here Bobby, what's up?\" regardless of what Bobby says. Core issue: Safari's MediaRecorder audio is not being properly captured/processed for Whisper.\n\n### Blocked\n- [ ] Guide: Sections 7-10 need content after questionnaire completion\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **HTML anchor format for clickable Telegram links**: `curl ... -d 'text=<a href=\"url\">label</a>&parse_mode=HTML'` — This is the ONLY format that reliably creates clickable hyperlinks in Telegram. OpenClaw's `presentation.blocks[].buttons[]` format doesn't support URL buttons (only callback_data).\n- **Tailscale URL for Telephone access**: `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/` — Bobby's iPhone can access this; localhost URLs don't work from the phone\n- **dean.js rewritten to use HTTP instead of shell curl**: Avoids shell syntax errors with emoji characters in the AI prompt. Sends proper HTTP POST to OpenClaw Gateway.\n- **dean.js now includes conversation history**: Passes recent messages context to AI so Dean doesn't just repeat \"what's up?\"\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Fix Telephone transcription** — Whisper keeps returning \"Could not transcribe\". Need to debug whether: (a) Safari MediaRecorder is capturing audio at all, (b) the multipart form-data parsing in server.js is corrupting the audio file, (c) ffmpeg conversion is failing, or (d) Whisper itself isn't processing the audio correctly. Test by recording audio directly on Mac and running through the same pipeline.\n2. **Get Bobby to fill out questionnaire** — `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/questionnaire.html`\n3. **Write Sections 7-10** — Fill in placeholder stubs, verify sections, assemble final guide\n4. **Compile PDF** — Use existing compiled HTML/WeasyPrint workflow\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Questionnaire**: `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/questionnaire.html` (port 8790 HTTP server)\n- **Telephone**: `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html` (same HTTP server, API on 8791)\n- **Telephone server**: Node.js on port 8791; dean.js polling on port 8787\n- **Telephone files**: `~/Desktop/Telephone/` — `telephone.html`, `server.js`, `dean.js`, `messages.json`, `audio/`\n- **dean.js logs**: `~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-dean.log`\n- **server.js logs**: `~/.openclaw/logs/telephone.log`\n- **TOOLS.md**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md`\n- **Guide folder**: `~/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/`\n- **Bobby's Telegram ID**: 8212808444\n- **Whisper transcription error**: Dean says \"I'm here Bobby. What's up?\" every time because transcription returns \"Could not transcribe\" — whisper is not processing Safari's MediaRecorder audio output correctly\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nFix transcription failing in a telephone app where Bobby speaks into his iPhone Safari browser, audio is captured via MediaRecorder, sent to server, but Whisper keeps returning \"Could not transcribe\".\n\n## Early Progress\n- Traced the issue: audio files (76KB webm) arrive at server but **ffmpeg fails to convert them** to mp3 format Whisper can process\n- Confirmed Whisper itself works fine on manually created audio (`say` command → test file → whisper successfully transcribed)\n- Suspected Safari on iOS isn't capturing audio properly through MediaRecorder, or the webm container format from Safari isn't compatible with the system's ffmpeg build\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe suffix shows final testing: verifying ffmpeg supports webm format (confirmed), and proving the transcription pipeline itself works by successfully converting and transcribing a known-good test audio file (test_speech.mp3). This confirms the problem is specifically with how Safari's MediaRecorder captures or encodes audio, not with whisper or ffmpeg in general.\n\n<read-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Progress-Notes.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-1-What-is-OpenClaw.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-10-Money-Making-Use-Cases.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-7-Your-First-Automation.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-8-Real-World-Workflows.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-9-Advanced-Techniques.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/questionnaire.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/poller.sh\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/server.js\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html\n/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.sh\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"adf43103","tokensBefore":114342,"details":{"readFiles":["/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Progress-Notes.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-1-What-is-OpenClaw.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-10-Money-Making-Use-Cases.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-7-Your-First-Automation.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-8-Real-World-Workflows.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-9-Advanced-Techniques.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/questionnaire.html","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/poller.sh","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/server.js","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html","/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.sh"]},"fromHook":false}
