{"type":"message","id":"bdde7e2e","parentId":"61993e69","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:34:17.359Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pipeline works fine with AIFF files sent directly. But Bobby's Safari sends audio as `audio/webm`. The server now receives raw binary and transcribes it. But let me check if Safari on iPhone sends audio in a way the server can handle.\n\nActually, looking at the server code - it receives raw binary with Content-Type: audio/webm. The issue might be that Safari's MediaRecorder sends chunks and the file might be getting cut off.\n\nLet me also check if the issue is the webm container format from Safari. The server writes the raw binary to a .webm file, and then ffmpeg tries to convert it. But maybe Safari's webm encoding is causing issues.\n\n\nI should test the webm conversion directly to see if that's where the problem lies. Also, I'm noticing Dean.js has been failing to connect to the gateway - it's hardcoded to port 18789 but my earlier test showed it returning \"Not found\". Let me verify the dean.js configuration is actually correct.\n","thinkingSignature":"41e06c5012c4815367b5a953c110682dc943650561da77412b5e8d2de3ab94d6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6l02tddarv73_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test webm format\nsay \"Testing webm audio format\" -o /tmp/webm_test.aiff\nffmpeg -i /tmp/webm_test.aiff /tmp/webm_test.webm -y 2>/dev/null\nls -la /tmp/webm_test.webm\n\n# Send as webm\necho \"Sending webm to server:\"\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:8791/talk \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: audio/webm\" \\\n  --data-binary @/tmp/webm_test.webm 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":954,"output":347,"cacheRead":62592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777667638452,"responseId":"0644413f267f70ed394013b7f0ea3715"}}
