{"type":"message","id":"d014f15d","parentId":"079187aa","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:45:45.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `gateway.http.endpoints` is empty — meaning the OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint isn't enabled. That's why we're getting \"Not Found\" — the endpoint doesn't exist.\n\nSo the dean.js can't reach the AI because the HTTP API endpoint isn't enabled.\n\nLet me think about the options:\n1. Enable the `gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions` config — but I need to be careful about security since `bind: loopback` is set, which means it's only accessible from localhost anyway\n2. Use a different approach to have Dean respond to Telephone messages\n\nSince `bind: loopback` and there's Tailscale auth, enabling the chat completions endpoint on port 18789 (localhost only) should be relatively safe. Let me enable it.\n","thinkingSignature":"b71a34ca934e0f0648b5db4804897a8b72361f647700df559d8c45c86820f704"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k0xmd7dzx0e5_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.schema.lookup","path":"gateway.http.endpoints.chatCompletions"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":165,"output":203,"cacheRead":65408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65776,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777668338720,"responseId":"064443f221d04fcf19711c4d1a016d4d"}}
