{"type":"message","id":"1324fb93","parentId":"a3b548a9","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:51:46.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The connection error is happening because the audio is being sent as `audio/mp4` (not `audio/webm`). The server is writing it as `mp4` but the transcription is working. The issue must be in the telephone.html frontend - it's receiving the connection error from the fetch.\n\nLet me look at the sendAudio function in telephone.html - it uses `Content-Type: audio/webm` but Safari is sending as `audio/mp4`. Actually wait - looking at the server log, the transcription DID work (\"What is the weather today?\"). So the audio WAS received and transcribed.\n\nThe \"connection error\" must be coming from the fetch to `/talk` timing out or failing for some other reason. \n\nThe server successfully transcribed the audio and returned a response, so the fetch completed and parsed correctly. The issue might be that Safari is sending a different audio format than expected, causing the server to reject it even though transcription worked.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the Content-Type mismatch is the real culprit here - the fetch is sending `audio/webm` but Safari is sending audio as `audio/mp4`. The server is writing it correctly as an mp4 file based on the content-type header, and the transcription succeeded, so the timing issue with the audio file being deleted before the next step might not be the problem. But then why is the frontend showing a connection error? I'm seeing \"audio/mp4\" in the logs when I was expecting \"audio/webm\" - the server is receiving a different format than my test was sending. Let me trace through what's actually happening with Safari's MediaRecorder output versus my test audio format.\n","thinkingSignature":"36f6a50656231f1a635b1923dcfc51f0a6d14fcddeeadb6b9d80f786872c87ff"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe audio IS getting through and transcribing — I can see it in the server logs. The \"connection error\" is in the browser after the fetch. Let me check the actual error:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lf9m9s44ynri_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8791/talk \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: audio/mp4\" \\\n  --data-binary @/tmp/weather_test.aiff 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":360,"output":440,"cacheRead":65152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65952,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777668698827,"responseId":"0644455bfe09740eacc53ade78b48006"}}
