{"type":"message","id":"a3e0c393","parentId":"e6ae271a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:52:33.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the curl test works. The issue must be something about the iPhone's audio format or network connection through Tailscale.\n\nLet me think about what could cause \"Connection error\" in the telephone.html sendAudio function:\n\n```javascript\nasync function sendAudio(blob) {\n  try {\n    const resp = await fetch('http://localhost:8791/talk', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'audio/webm' },\n      body: blob\n    });\n    ...\n  } catch(e) {\n    status.textContent = 'Connection error';\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe fetch is going to `localhost:8791`. But on iPhone, `localhost` refers to the iPhone itself, not the Mac! That's the problem.\n\nI need to change the fetch URL from `localhost:8791` to the Mac's IP address or Tailscale URL.\n\nThe HTTP server on port 8790 serves the HTML. But the API calls go to localhost which doesn't work from the iPhone.\n\nI need to change all the fetch URLs in telephone.html to point to the Mac's IP or Tailscale address. But wait - the Tailscale URL is HTTPS and the API server is HTTP (not HTTPS). Also, if I use the Tailscale domain, the browser on iPhone will try to reach it from the iPhone's network, not from the Mac.\n \nThe cleanest approach is to have all API calls go through the HTTP server on port 8790, which acts as a proxy and can forward requests to the backend on 8791. This way the iPhone only needs to connect to one port. Looking at the Python server that's currently running on 8790, I can update it to proxy the `/talk` endpoint to the API server instead of having the iPhone make direct requests to different ports.\n","thinkingSignature":"251b0d711a480a0610bbb9a39d658034c5f51072bd338f86c79302bf29aa8b26"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe iPhone is trying to reach `localhost:8791` — but localhost on your phone is your phone, not the Mac. All API calls need to go through the HTTP server on port 8790 (which proxies to 8791). Let me fix the HTML to use the correct URL.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7p17fzs78hq8_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no\">\n  <title>Telephone — Dean</title>\n  <style>\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    body {\n      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n      background: #0a0a0f;\n      color: #e0e0e0;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      overflow: hidden;\n      user-select: none;\n      -webkit-user-select: none;\n    }\n\n    #fairy-canvas {\n      position: fixed;\n      top: 0; left: 0;\n      width: 100%; height: 100%;\n      z-index: 0;\n      pointer-events: none;\n    }\n\n    .ui {\n      position: relative;\n      z-index: 1;\n      display: flex;\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      gap: 20px;\n      padding: 20px;\n    }\n\n    .dean-status {\n      font-size: 16px;\n      font-weight: 500;\n      letter-spacing: 1px;\n      color: #666;\n      min-height: 24px;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n    }\n\n    .dean-status.listening { color: #ff6b6b; }\n    .dean-status.thinking { color: #ffd93d; }\n    .dean-status.replying { color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .mic-btn {\n      width: 120px;\n      height: 120px;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 3px solid #333;\n      background: #1a1a24;\n      cursor: pointer;\n      display: flex;\n      align-items: center;\n      justify-content: center;\n      transition: all 0.15s;\n      position: relative;\n      -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn:active, .mic-btn.on { \n      border-color: #ff6b6b; \n      background: #2a1a1a; \n      transform: scale(0.96);\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn svg {\n      width: 44px;\n      height: 44px;\n      fill: #666;\n      transition: fill 0.15s;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on svg { fill: #ff6b6b; }\n\n    .pulse-ring {\n      position: absolute;\n      width: 100%;\n      height: 100%;\n      border-radius: 50%;\n      border: 2px solid #ff6b6b;\n      opacity: 0;\n    }\n\n    .mic-btn.on .pulse-ring { animation: pulse 1.5s ease-out infinite; }\n\n    @keyframes pulse {\n      0% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 0.8; }\n      100% { transform: scale(1.8); opacity: 0; }\n    }\n\n    .transcript-area {\n      background: #111118;\n      border: 1px solid #222;\n      border-radius: 12px;\n      padding: 16px 20px;\n      max-width: 360px;\n      width: 100%;\n      min-height: 80px;\n      max-height: 200px;\n      overflow-y: auto;\n    }\n\n    .transcript-line {\n      font-size: 15px;\n      line-height: 1.5;\n      color: #888;\n    }\n\n    .transcript-line.user { color: #ff6b6b; }\n    .transcript-line.dean { color: #6bffb8; }\n\n    .hint {\n      font-size: 12px;\n      color: #333;\n      text-align: center;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<canvas id=\"fairy-canvas\"></canvas>\n\n<div class=\"ui\">\n  <div class=\"dean-status\" id=\"status\">Tap mic to talk</div>\n\n  <button class=\"mic-btn\" id=\"mic-btn\">\n    <div class=\"pulse-ring\"></div>\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M12 14c1.66 0 3-1.34 3-3V5c0-1.66-1.34-3-3-3S9 3.34 9 5v6c0 1.66 1.34 3 3 3zm5.91-3c-.49 0-.9.36-.98.85C16.52 14.2 14.47 16 12 16s-4.52-1.8-4.93-4.15c-.08-.49-.49-.85-.98-.85-.61 0-1.09.54-1 1.14.49 3 2.89 5.35 5.91 5.78V20c0 .55.45 1 1 1s1-.45 1-1v-2.08c3.02-.43 5.42-2.78 5.91-5.78.1-.6-.39-1.14-1-1.14z\"/></svg>\n  </button>\n\n  <div class=\"transcript-area\" id=\"transcript-area\">\n    <div class=\"transcript-line\" id=\"transcript\">—</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"hint\">Hold to record • Release to send</div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n// === API Base URL ===\n// All API calls go through the HTTP server (port 8790) which proxies to 8791\n// Using this page's own host to handle both localhost (Mac) and remote (iPhone) access\nconst API_BASE = '';  // Use relative URLs so it works from any host\n\n// === Fairy Lights ===\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('fairy-canvas');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nlet lights = [];\nlet mode = 'idle';\n\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\n  canvas.width = window.innerWidth;\n  canvas.height = window.innerHeight;\n}\nresizeCanvas();\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\n\nconst NUM_LIGHTS = 55;\nfor (let i = 0; i < NUM_LIGHTS; i++) {\n  lights.push({\n    x: Math.random() * canvas.width,\n    y: Math.random() * canvas.height,\n    vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4,\n    vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4,\n    size: Math.random() * 2.5 + 1,\n    brightness: Math.random() * 0.5 + 0.3,\n    hue: Math.random() * 50 + 15,\n    twinkle: Math.random() * Math.PI * 2,\n    twinkleSpeed: Math.random() * 0.04 + 0.015\n  });\n}\n\nfunction drawLight(l, intensity) {\n  const alpha = l.brightness * intensity;\n  ctx.save();\n  ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;\n  ctx.fillStyle = `hsl(${l.hue}, 80%, 70%)`;\n  ctx.shadowBlur = 12 * intensity;\n  ctx.shadowColor = `hsl(${l.hue}, 90%, 60%)`;\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  ctx.arc(l.x, l.y, l.size * (0.8 + intensity * 0.3), 0, Math.PI * 2);\n  ctx.fill();\n  ctx.restore();\n}\n\nfunction updateLights() {\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    l.x += l.vx;\n    l.y += l.vy;\n    l.twinkle += l.twinkleSpeed;\n    if (l.x < 0 || l.x > canvas.width) l.vx *= -1;\n    if (l.y < 0 || l.y > canvas.height) l.vy *= -1;\n    l.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.01;\n    l.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.01;\n    l.vx = Math.max(-0.8, Math.min(0.8, l.vx));\n    l.vy = Math.max(-0.8, Math.min(0.8, l.vy));\n  }\n}\n\nfunction getIntensity() {\n  if (mode === 'listening') return 1.8;\n  if (mode === 'replying') return 2.2;\n  if (mode === 'thinking') return 0.3 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.004) * 0.4;\n  return 0.7 + Math.sin(Date.now() * 0.001) * 0.1;\n}\n\nfunction animate() {\n  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n  updateLights();\n  const intensity = getIntensity();\n  for (let l of lights) {\n    const tw = 0.7 + Math.sin(l.twinkle) * 0.3;\n    drawLight(l, intensity * tw);\n  }\n  requestAnimationFrame(animate);\n}\nanimate();\n\n// === Mic Recording ===\nconst micBtn = document.getElementById('mic-btn');\nconst status = document.getElementById('status');\nconst transcriptEl = document.getElementById('transcript');\nconst transcriptArea = document.getElementById('transcript-area');\n\nlet mediaRecorder = null;\nlet audioChunks = [];\nlet isRecording = false;\nlet audioStream = null;\nlet lastChecked = 0;\n\nfunction setStatus(text, cls) {\n  status.textContent = text;\n  status.className = 'dean-status ' + (cls || '');\n}\n\nfunction addTranscript(text, who) {\n  const lines = transcriptArea.querySelectorAll('.transcript-line');\n  if (lines.length >= 6) lines[0].remove();\n  \n  const el = document.createElement('div');\n  el.className = 'transcript-line ' + who;\n  el.textContent = (who === 'user' ? 'You: ' : 'Dean: ') + text;\n  transcriptArea.appendChild(el);\n  transcriptArea.scrollTop = transcriptArea.scrollHeight;\n}\n\nasync function startRecording() {\n  try {\n    audioStream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ \n      audio: {\n        echoCancellation: true,\n        noiseSuppression: true,\n        autoGainControl: true\n      }\n    });\n  } catch(e) {\n    setStatus('Mic denied', '');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  isRecording = true;\n  mode = 'listening';\n  micBtn.classList.add('on');\n  setStatus('Listening', 'listening');\n  audioChunks = [];\n\n  const mimeType = MediaRecorder.isTypeSupported('audio/webm;codecs=opus') \n    ? 'audio/webm;codecs=opus' \n    : 'audio/webm';\n\n  mediaRecorder = new MediaRecorder(audioStream, { mimeType });\n\n  mediaRecorder.ondataavailable = (event) => {\n    if (event.data && event.data.size > 0) {\n      audioChunks.push(event.data);\n    }\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onstop = async () => {\n    const blob = new Blob(audioChunks, { type: mimeType });\n    audioChunks = [];\n    await sendAudio(blob, mimeType);\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.onerror = (e) => {\n    setStatus('Recording error', '');\n    isRecording = false;\n    micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n  };\n\n  mediaRecorder.start();\n}\n\nfunction stopRecording() {\n  if (!isRecording || !mediaRecorder) return;\n  isRecording = false;\n  micBtn.classList.remove('on');\n  setStatus('Processing', '');\n\n  if (mediaRecorder.state !== 'inactive') mediaRecorder.stop();\n  if (audioStream) audioStream.getTracks().forEach(t => t.stop());\n}\n\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mousedown', startRecording);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); startRecording(); });\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mouseup', stopRecording);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('mouseleave', stopRecording);\nmicBtn.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => { e.preventDefault(); stopRecording(); });\n\nasync function sendAudio(blob, mimeType) {\n  try {\n    const resp = await fetch(API_BASE + '/talk', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': mimeType },\n      body: blob\n    });\n\n    const data = await resp.json();\n    \n    if (data.transcript) {\n      addTranscript(data.transcript, 'user');\n    }\n\n    if (data.received) {\n      mode = 'thinking';\n      setStatus('Dean thinking', 'thinking');\n      pollForReply();\n    } else {\n      setStatus('Try again', '');\n      mode = 'idle';\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('Send error:', e);\n    setStatus('Connection error', '');\n    mode = 'idle';\n  }\n}\n\nasync function pollForReply() {\n  const poll = async () => {\n    try {\n      const resp = await fetch(API_BASE + '/messages?since=' + lastChecked);\n      const data = await resp.json();\n\n      const deanMsg = data.messages?.find(m => m.from === 'dean');\n      if (deanMsg && deanMsg.audioFile) {\n        lastChecked = Math.max(lastChecked, deanMsg.timestamp);\n        \n        mode = 'replying';\n        setStatus('Dean replying', 'replying');\n        addTranscript(deanMsg.text, 'dean');\n\n        const audio = new Audio(API_BASE + deanMsg.audioFile);\n        audio.play();\n\n        audio.onended = () => {\n          mode = 'idle';\n          setStatus('Tap mic to talk', '');\n        };\n\n        audio.onerror = () => {\n          mode = 'idle';\n          setStatus('Tap mic to talk', '');\n        };\n\n        return;\n      }\n\n      setTimeout(poll, 1500);\n    } catch(e) {\n      setTimeout(poll, 2000);\n    }\n  };\n  poll();\n}\n\n// Load existing messages\nfetch(API_BASE + '/messages?since=0')\n  .then(r => r.json())\n  .then(d => {\n    d.messages?.forEach(m => {\n      lastChecked = Math.max(lastChecked, m.timestamp);\n      if (m.text) addTranscript(m.text, m.from);\n    });\n  });\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/telephone.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":174,"output":3643,"cacheRead":65536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69353,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777668721230,"responseId":"06444571eefe5f0016431ae48f54a2bc"}}
