{"type":"message","id":"772860db","parentId":"d7ee6b96","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:52:43.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is the API_BASE is empty, so it's trying to fetch `/talk` which would go to port 8790 (the Python HTTP server) instead of port 8791 (the Node.js API server). The Python HTTP server on 8790 only serves static files - it doesn't have the `/talk` endpoint.\n\nI need to change the approach. The telephone.html is served from port 8790, but the API is on port 8791. The relative URL `/talk` would go to port 8790, not 8791.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Explicitly use port 8791 in the URLs (but this won't work from iPhone since 8791 is not accessible through Tailscale - only 8790 is port-forwarded)\n\n\n2. Have the Python HTTP server proxy /talk and /messages requests to the Node.js API server on 8791\n3. Change the API_BASE to point to the right port\n\nLet me check what's actually running on these ports - the Python HTTP server is on 8790 serving the static HTML, but the Node server on 8791 is handling the API calls. The iPhone connects through Tailscale to the HTTP server, but the API calls need to reach the Node server instead.\n\nI need to either set up a proxy in the HTTP server to forward API requests to 8791, or explicitly configure the API_BASE to use port 8791.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully, there's only one audio file and no new connections showing up, which suggests the request isn't even reaching the server.\n\nActually, I see the issue now - the telephone.html is served from port 8790, but when the iPhone tries to fetch `/talk`, it's making that request to port 8790 instead of 8791 where the actual server is running. The HTTP server on 8790 doesn't have a `/talk` endpoint, so it returns a 404 or connection error. I need to either set up a proxy on 8790 to forward those API calls to 8791, or change the URL to explicitly point to port 8791. I realize I can't specify a port in a fetch URL when using relative paths with Tailscale, so I need to set up a proxy on the HTTP server instead to forward /talk and /messages requests to port 8791.\n","thinkingSignature":"3dad0fb00544cbc5772389aff8ee675933972ecfacd372ab7e8beab559c8c9ff"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rjhv0o3951zo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# The Python HTTP server on 8790 proxies to 8791\n# Check what the proxy config looks like\nps aux | grep \"59062\\|python.*8790\" | grep -v grep | head -3\nlsof -i :8790 | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3346,"output":563,"cacheRead":65600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69509,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777668754164,"responseId":"06444592b03dd6efcc96368c07dec9a8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"48c02be1","parentId":"772860db","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:52:45.091Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rjhv0o3951zo_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"bobbygalletta    59062   0.0  0.0 442200064   2336   ??  SN    4:09PM   0:00.52 /opt/homebrew/Cellar/python@3.14/3.14.4/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/Resources/Python.app/Contents/MacOS/Python -m http.server 8790 --bind 0.0.0.0\nCOMMAND   PID          USER   FD   TYPE             DEVICE SIZE/OFF NODE NAME\nPython  59062 bobbygalletta    3u  IPv4 0xd4a66f11d5803301      0t0  TCP *:8790 (LISTEN)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":928,"aggregated":"bobbygalletta    59062   0.0  0.0 442200064   2336   ??  SN    4:09PM   0:00.52 /opt/homebrew/Cellar/python@3.14/3.14.4/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/Resources/Python.app/Contents/MacOS/Python -m http.server 8790 --bind 0.0.0.0\nCOMMAND   PID          USER   FD   TYPE             DEVICE SIZE/OFF NODE NAME\nPython  59062 bobbygalletta    3u  IPv4 0xd4a66f11d5803301      0t0  TCP *:8790 (LISTEN)","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777668765085}}
{"type":"message","id":"196748fd","parentId":"48c02be1","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:52:52.197Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Python HTTP server is just a basic file server - it doesn't proxy to 8791. I need to make the API calls go to the right port.\n\nFor the iPhone, `API_BASE = ''` (relative URL) will use port 8790 (the current page's port), but the API is on 8791.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Have the Python server proxy API calls to 8791\n2. Or have the phone access port 8791 directly (but Python's simple http.server serves files on 8790)\n\nActually, the simplest fix: use port 8791 for the API URL directly since it's an API server, not a file server. The phone should hit:\n- Page: https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html (served by Python on 8790)\n\n\n- API: https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net:8791/talk (Node API on 8791)\n\nBut Tailscale serves on 443 by default... I need to check how the Tailscale serve is configured.\n","thinkingSignature":"8971a3e592d4188f508ef44fc3a82f181196ad3308defbd2a260a4d27bfcc6b5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_syw0vjdbc91z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check tailscale serve config\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(json.dumps(d.get('gateway',{}).get('tailscale',{}), indent=2))\n\" 2>/dev/null\n\n# What port is tailscale actually serving on externally?\n# Check what ports are accessible via the tailscale URL\ncurl -s --max-time 3 http://localhost:8791/health 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":340,"output":365,"cacheRead":68864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69569,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777668765211,"responseId":"0644459d0c2ed9ac3fda961b82ac0cf8"}}
