{"type":"message","id":"b49b68e7","parentId":"4c978c32","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:52:59.213Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The health check on 8791 works, but port 8791 is NOT on the tailscale URL. The tailscale URL only serves the gateway port 18789.\n\nBut wait - the Python HTTP server on 8790 IS bound to `0.0.0.0` which means it should be accessible externally. Let me check if it's actually reachable from outside.\n\nActually wait - the Python server was started manually, not through OpenClaw. OpenClaw's tailscale serve only exposes the gateway port. So the Tailscale URL `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/` goes to gateway port 18789.\n \nThe HTTP server on 8790 is bound to all interfaces though, so it should be reachable at `http://localhost:8790/` locally and potentially from the Tailscale network at `http://100.85.83.52:8790/` if that IP is accessible to the iPhone.\n\nActually, I should clarify how OpenClaw's tailscale serve actually works—it might not be a simple port forward but rather routing through the gateway itself, which could explain why only port 18789 is exposed despite the HTTP server binding to all interfaces.\n","thinkingSignature":"e6aca97dcdd7501977c35440b27fe61e29963b0ffe9b59f2b3fe77530fdc8ed4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eho0p9encfsl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if iPhone can reach port 8790 via Tailscale\n# First, what's the tailscale IP?\nip addr show | grep -A2 tailscale 2>/dev/null | head -5\n# Can we reach 8790 from the tailscale IP?\ncurl -s --max-time 3 http://100.85.83.52:8790/ 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":254,"output":366,"cacheRead":69120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69740,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777668772429,"responseId":"064445a429961a98cad2ba702a4e3585"}}
