{"type":"message","id":"30fde49a","parentId":"5324150d","timestamp":"2026-05-01T21:10:17.159Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The minimax provider uses oauth, not an api key directly. Let me check if I can use the gateway's session-based AI calls instead - maybe there's a tool I can use to call the AI directly rather than hitting the /v1/chat/completions endpoint.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. Instead of trying to call the AI through the gateway (which seems to have the /v1/chat/completions endpoint disabled), maybe I should:\n\n1. Use a different approach - call the minimax API directly using the OAuth token that's already configured\n2. Or check if there's another way to get AI responses\n\nActually wait - I remember from the config that minimax uses OAuth, meaning it's using the user's account. The `apiKey` field shows \"minimax-oauth\" which suggests it's a reference to an OAuth flow rather than a static key.\n\nLet me try a different approach: instead of fixing the AI integration (which is complex), let me first understand what Bobby actually wants.\n\nBobby wants a voice app where he can have a \"normal conversation\" and \"get things done.\" The current system:\n1. ✓ Captures voice\n2. ✓ Transcribes with Whisper\n3. ✓ Responds with contextual pre-scripted responses\n4. ✗ Can't actually do tasks (weather, email, etc.) - just pretends to\n\nThe core issue is: Dean can't actually DO anything. He's just responding with words but not taking actions.\n\nFor Telephone to be \"live\" and actually useful, Dean needs to:\n1. Actually check weather (not just say \"let me check the weather\")\n2. Actually send messages, check email, etc.\n\nBut integrating with all those services from a standalone Node.js script is complex. The real power would be using OpenClaw's tools for this.\n\nThe gateway has tools like `gateway` tool, `sessions_send` tool, etc. But the /v1/chat/completions endpoint is disabled.\n\n\nI'm hitting a wall with the endpoint configuration and OAuth setup. Rather than wrestling with API credentials and endpoint permissions, I should focus on what Telephone can actually do reliably right now. The core problem isn't the AI integration—it's that the system can't execute real tasks. Let me prioritize building something that actually works before trying to add more complexity.\n","thinkingSignature":"987a2940df69d5da82b62546c2b3580aa6af2301a18e198375bc1eda8c6eff73"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe issue isn't just the AI — it's that Dean **says** he'll check weather/email but doesn't actually DO anything. That's why it feels fake.\n\nTo make Telephone truly \"live\" and useful, Dean needs to actually:\n- Check real weather\n- Read your calendar\n- Send messages\n- etc.\n\nThat requires connecting to OpenClaw's tools. The problem is the `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint is disabled on the gateway.\n\n**Quick question:** What's more important to you right now:\n\n1. **Fix the AI so Dean responds smarter** (even if he still can't do real tasks) — I can enable the chat completions endpoint\n\n2. **Make Dean actually DO things** (weather, calendar, reminders) — this needs more setup but would be genuinely useful\n\n3. **Both** — fix AI responses AND make him functional\n\nOption 3 would be the real Telephone you described — voice-first, can actually get things done. But it takes more time to wire up all the integrations.\n\nWhat do you want to prioritize?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":192,"output":687,"cacheRead":85440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86319,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777669798366,"responseId":"064449a630e93f343af63a65b4763041"}}
