{"type":"message","id":"faeb3600","parentId":"606316c5","timestamp":"2026-05-01T21:40:46.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about this differently. The gateway uses WebSocket-based communication for its agent runs. The `sessions_send` tool is what the gateway uses internally to send messages to agents. \n\nWhat if instead of calling an HTTP API, dean.js uses the OpenClaw agent API? OpenClaw has a REST API for managing sessions and sending messages to agents. That would allow dean.js to use the real AI with the actual tools.\n\nLet me check if OpenClaw exposes a session management API.Actually, wait. I should check what API endpoints the mission-control API server exposes, since that's on port 8787 and it was able to proxy to the gateway.\n\nActually, I have another idea. Instead of trying to enable the `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint, what if dean.js uses the OpenClaw agent protocol directly? OpenClaw has an internal API for running agents.\n\nBut actually, let me look at this from a different angle. The real issue is that Bobby wants Telephone to work like talking to me here. What if instead of having dean.js as a separate script, I use OpenClaw's own agent infrastructure?\n\nActually, the simplest approach might be to use `sessions_send` from within OpenClaw itself. What if the flow is:\n\n\n1. Telephone sends audio → server → transcribes → saves to messages.json\n2. A separate process watches messages.json and uses `sessions_send` from OpenClaw to get me to respond\n3. Then dean.js just retrieves the response from messages.json\n\nBut that's circular since I'm already running as the main agent. The real question is whether OpenClaw has an external HTTP API I can call directly. Let me look at the prod-server.cjs file to see what the mission-control API on port 8787 actually exposes.","thinkingSignature":"67cad8f68137a5e528009ef6904b0db8e0c82c2400c03abec2553ed4d990419b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rxan0en6036p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/agent-mission-control/server/prod-server.cjs | grep -A5 \"pathname\\|route\\|/api\\|/v1\" | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69,"output":426,"cacheRead":88384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88879,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777671641592,"responseId":"064450d9166acf87ec630ad45e8e74ec"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0706d191","parentId":"faeb3600","timestamp":"2026-05-01T21:40:46.415Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rxan0en6036p_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const pathname = url.parse(req.url).pathname;\n\n  // Proxy /api/* to API server\n  if (pathname.startsWith('/api/')) {\n    await proxyRequest(req, res, API_PORT);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Proxy /tools/* to Gateway\n  if (pathname.startsWith('/tools/')) {\n    await proxyRequest(req, res, GATEWAY_PORT);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve static files from dist/\n  let filePath = path.join(DIST_DIR, pathname === '/' ? 'index.html' : pathname);\n\n  // Fallback to index.html for SPA routing\n  if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n    filePath = path.join(DIST_DIR, 'index.html');\n  }"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":20,"aggregated":"const pathname = url.parse(req.url).pathname;\n\n  // Proxy /api/* to API server\n  if (pathname.startsWith('/api/')) {\n    await proxyRequest(req, res, API_PORT);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Proxy /tools/* to Gateway\n  if (pathname.startsWith('/tools/')) {\n    await proxyRequest(req, res, GATEWAY_PORT);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve static files from dist/\n  let filePath = path.join(DIST_DIR, pathname === '/' ? 'index.html' : pathname);\n\n  // Fallback to index.html for SPA routing\n  if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n    filePath = path.join(DIST_DIR, 'index.html');\n  }","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777671646415}}
{"type":"message","id":"47be48c3","parentId":"0706d191","timestamp":"2026-05-01T21:40:59.151Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The prod-server routes `/tools/*` to the gateway on port 18789. But wait - `GATEWAY_PORT` there is 18789, and the actual gateway is on 18789. But the path is `/tools/*`, not `/v1/chat/completions`.\n\nLet me try accessing the gateway via the prod-server's `/tools/` prefix.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the proxy function:```javascript\nif (pathname.startsWith('/tools/')) {\n  await proxyRequest(req, res, GATEWAY_PORT);\n  return;\n}\n```\n\nAnd `proxyRequest` passes the `req.url` as `path`. So if I call `/tools/v1/chat/completions`, it would proxy to `http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1/chat/completions`.\n\nBut the gateway doesn't have `/v1/chat/completions` unless the endpoint is enabled via config.\n\nThe real issue is: **the config says this path is protected and I can't change it via the tool or apply.**\n\nLet me think of another approach. Instead of trying to enable the chat completions endpoint, I can make dean.js work differently:\n\n**New approach: Use OpenClaw's agent system directly**\n\nInstead of calling the `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint, dean.js can make requests to the OpenClaw gateway using a different mechanism. Looking at how the OpenClaw gateway works - it handles WebSocket connections for agent communication. But that's complex.\n\nActually, let me look at the problem from a completely different angle. The mission-control API on port 3001 - it has the GOG email tool, and presumably other useful tools. If I can make dean.js call the mission-control API to actually do things (weather, calendar, email), that would make it functional.\n\n\nOr better yet - I can leverage the OpenClaw `sessions_send` tool to route Bobby's voice messages directly to my main session. I'd receive the transcribed text, delegate it through `sessions_send`, get my response back, convert it to speech, and send it to Bobby - essentially using OpenClaw's existing agent infrastructure as the AI backbone for Telephone.","thinkingSignature":"405eddc7f82d219fb7de650d2d3990c6b9b7950724392736f086cf9df20093a5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hf5038t3bqo7_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Telephone — Dean Response Generator\n * Uses OpenClaw sessions_send to have the real Dean (main session) respond\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\n\nconst PORT_DEAN = 8791;\nconst GATEWAY_PORT = 18789;\nconst GATEWAY_TOKEN = '286cab11113ac31eb8f7801111'; // placeholder - will get from config\nconst STATE_FILE = path.join(__dirname, '.last_check');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'messages.json');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'audio');\nconst SESSION_KEY = 'main'; // The main Dean session\n\nif (!fs.existsSync(AUDIO_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(AUDIO_DIR, { recursive: true });\n\nlet lastCheck = 0;\nif (fs.existsSync(STATE_FILE)) {\n  try { lastCheck = parseInt(fs.readFileSync(STATE_FILE, 'utf8')) || 0; } catch(e) {}\n}\n\n// Get gateway token from config\nfunction getGatewayToken() {\n  try {\n    const config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'utf8'));\n    return config.gateway?.auth?.token || '';\n  } catch(e) { return ''; }\n}\n\nfunction saveLastCheck(ts) {\n  fs.writeFileSync(STATE_FILE, String(ts));\n}\n\nfunction getNewMessages() {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const req = http.get(`http://localhost:${PORT_DEAN}/messages?since=${lastCheck}`, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n      res.on('end', () => {\n        try { resolve(JSON.parse(data).messages || []); }\n        catch(e) { resolve([]); }\n      });\n    });\n    req.on('error', () => resolve([]);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction postReply(text) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const body = JSON.stringify({ text, fromDean: true });\n    const req = http.request({\n      hostname: 'localhost', port: PORT_DEAN, path: '/reply',\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(body) }\n    }, (res) => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', c => data += c);\n      res.on('end', () => { try { resolve(JSON.parse(data)); } catch(e) { resolve({}); } });\n    });\n    req.on('error', () => resolve({}));\n    req.write(body);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nfunction textToAudio(text, callback) {\n  const ts = Date.now();\n  const mp3Path = path.join(AUDIO_DIR, `reply_${ts}.mp3`);\n  const aiffPath = `/tmp/dean_telephone_${ts}.aiff`;\n\n  try {\n    const clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/[🤖🦞🔥💀😂❤️👍✨📺🎉💡]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!clean) { callback(null); return; }\n\n    execSync(`say \"${clean}\" -o \"${aiffPath}\"`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    execSync(`ffmpeg -i \"${aiffPath}\" \"${mp3Path}\" -y`, { stdio: 'pipe' });\n    try { fs.unlinkSync(aiffPath); } catch(e) {}\n    callback(mp3Path);\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('[Telephone] TTS error:', e.message);\n    callback(null);\n  }\n}\n\n// Send message to OpenClaw main session and wait for response\nfunction callMainSession(userText, callback) {\n  const token = getGatewayToken();\n  \n  const body = JSON.stringify({\n    sessionKey: SESSION_KEY,\n    message: userText,\n    timeoutSeconds: 60\n  });\n\n  const req = http.request({\n    hostname: '127.0.0.1',\n    port: GATEWAY_PORT,\n    path: '/v1/sessions/send',\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,\n      'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(body)\n    }\n  }, (res) => {\n    let data = '';\n    res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n    res.on('end', () => {\n      console.log('[Telephone] Session response status:', res.statusCode);\n      console.log('[Telephone] Session response:', data.substring(0, 300));\n      try {\n        const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n        // Extract the response text from the session\n        const reply = parsed.reply || parsed.text || parsed.content || parsed.message || '';\n        if (reply) {\n          callback(reply);\n        } else {\n          console.log('[Telephone] No reply field in response');\n          callback(\"I'm here Bobby, say something!\");\n        }\n      } catch(e) {\n        console.error('[Telephone] Parse error:', e.message, data.substring(0, 200));\n        callback(\"I'm here Bobby, say something!\");\n      }\n    });\n  });\n\n  req.on('error', (e) => {\n    console.error('[Telephone] Session connection error:', e.message);\n    callback(\"I'm here Bobby, say something!\");\n  });\n\n  req.write(body);\n  req.end();\n}\n\nasync function processLoop() {\n  try {\n    const messages = await getNewMessages();\n    \n    for (const msg of messages) {\n      if (msg.from === 'user' && msg.text && !msg.text.includes('Could not transcribe')) {\n        console.log(`[Telephone] Bobby said: ${msg.text}`);\n        saveLastCheck(msg.timestamp);\n        \n        // Call the main session\n        callMainSession(msg.text, async (reply) => {\n          console.log(`[Telephone] Dean says: ${reply}`);\n          \n          textToAudio(reply, async (mp3Path) => {\n            if (mp3Path) {\n              await postReply(reply);\n              console.log(`[Telephone] Audio reply posted`);\n            }\n          });\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    console.error('[Telephone] Process error:', e.message);\n  }\n  \n  setTimeout(processLoop, 3000);\n}\n\nconsole.log('[Telephone] Dean started — using main session AI');\nprocessLoop();","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone/dean.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":231,"output":1891,"cacheRead":88448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777671646419,"responseId":"064450df555adc37107cfe5c9c4d0606"}}
