{"type":"message","id":"43905e14","parentId":"b6931956","timestamp":"2026-05-01T22:53:04.835Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The screenshot shows \"TRY AGAIN\" and I can see from the logs that Bobby said \"Hello Dean, how are you?\" multiple times, meaning:\n\n1. The iPhone IS connecting to the server successfully\n2. The transcription IS working (\"Hello Dean, how are you?\" is being transcribed)\n3. Dean IS responding with audio replies\n\nBut the page shows \"TRY AGAIN\" - which means the audio playback is failing. Bobby isn't hearing the replies. The issue is likely:\n- The audio files are at `/audio/reply_xxx.mp3`\n- When the phone requests `http://localhost:8791/audio/reply.mp3`, it can't reach localhost from the iPhone\n\n\n- The proxy isn't correctly routing `/audio/xxx` requests to the API server, so the iPhone gets a 404 when trying to fetch the audio file, triggering the \"TRY AGAIN\" error\n\nI need to fix the proxy to properly forward audio file requests from the iPhone to the API server at localhost:8791.","thinkingSignature":"8e9cb8c4ff38087200007c9d9493969d9207baeb45a7cb1e4121e65517a27e90"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w5ge6xg1srcc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -10 ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-http.log 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# Check the audio URL issue\ncurl -s http://localhost:8790/audio/reply_1777672116473.mp3 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":99162,"output":291,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99581,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777675977725,"responseId":"064461caae26adc6eddf35c28c217abf"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2d0b77a","parentId":"43905e14","timestamp":"2026-05-01T22:53:05.083Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_w5ge6xg1srcc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTP proxy running on 8790, proxying to 8791\n(node:16863) [DEP0169] DeprecationWarning: `url.parse()` behavior is not standardized and prone to errors that have security implications. Use the WHATWG URL API instead. CVEs are not issued for `url.parse()` vulnerabilities.\n(Use `node --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)\n---"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":34,"aggregated":"HTTP proxy running on 8790, proxying to 8791\n(node:16863) [DEP0169] DeprecationWarning: `url.parse()` behavior is not standardized and prone to errors that have security implications. Use the WHATWG URL API instead. CVEs are not issued for `url.parse()` vulnerabilities.\n(Use `node --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)\n---","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777675985083}}
{"type":"message","id":"d97b8295","parentId":"e2d0b77a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T22:53:13.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The HTTP proxy doesn't serve audio files! The audio files are on the API server (8791) but the proxy (8790) only proxies `/talk`, `/messages`, and `/reply` - it doesn't serve the static audio files. That's why Bobby sees \"Try Again\" - the audio file URL points to something like `/audio/reply_xxx.mp3` but the proxy doesn't handle that.\n\nLet me fix the proxy to also serve static audio files from the audio directory.","thinkingSignature":"60b05a4a1a88dfca8f083cf185fc02c69bae5d16b913ba43f56a07192c3e7e6b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m73e31nn2aoq_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst url = require('url');\n\nconst HTTP_PORT = 8790;\nconst API_PORT = 8791;\nconst DIR = '/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/Telephone';\n\nconst MIME_TYPES = {\n  '.html': 'text/html',\n  '.js': 'application/javascript',\n  '.css': 'text/css',\n  '.mp3': 'audio/mpeg',\n  '.json': 'application/json'\n};\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(204);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const pathname = url.parse(req.url).pathname;\n\n  // Proxy API calls to 8791\n  if (pathname.startsWith('/talk') || pathname.startsWith('/messages') || pathname.startsWith('/reply')) {\n    const options = {\n      hostname: '127.0.0.1',\n      port: API_PORT,\n      path: pathname + (req.url.includes('?') ? '?' + req.url.split('?')[1] : ''),\n      method: req.method,\n      headers: { ...req.headers }\n    };\n\n    const proxyReq = http.request(options, (proxyRes) => {\n      res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, proxyRes.headers);\n      proxyRes.pipe(res);\n    });\n\n    proxyReq.on('error', (e) => {\n      res.writeHead(502);\n      res.end('Proxy error');\n    });\n\n    req.pipe(proxyReq);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve audio files from the audio directory\n  if (pathname.startsWith('/audio/')) {\n    const filename = pathname.replace('/audio/', '');\n    const filePath = path.join(DIR, 'audio', filename);\n    if (fs.existsSync(filePath)) {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'audio/mpeg' });\n      fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n    } else {\n      res.writeHead(404);\n      res.end('Not found');\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve static files\n  let filePath = path.join(DIR, pathname === '/' ? '/telephone.html' : pathname);\n  if (!fs.existsSync(filePath) || !fs.statSync(filePath).isFile()) {\n    res.writeHead(404);\n    res.end('Not found');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const ext = path.extname(filePath);\n  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': MIME_TYPES[ext] || 'text/plain' });\n  fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n});\n\nserver.listen(HTTP_PORT, '0.0.0.0', () => {\n  console.log('HTTP proxy running on ' + HTTP_PORT + ', proxying to ' + API_PORT);\n});","path":"/tmp/proxy.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":206,"output":784,"cacheRead":99264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100254,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777675985086,"responseId":"064461d1b70ad0840e8dfc5ccd59c5f5"}}
