{"type":"message","id":"0fd1809c","parentId":"cff30a77","timestamp":"2026-05-01T22:53:22.678Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The proxy is now correctly serving audio files too! The test shows:\n- Audio file exists (19KB)\n- curl returns the MP3 binary data starting with \"ID3\" (MP3 header)\n\nThe problem was the old proxy only proxied /talk, /messages, /reply but didn't serve static audio files directly. Now the proxy serves both API calls AND static files.\n\nLet me also check the telephone.html to make sure the audio URL paths are correct for both local and remote access.\n\nIn telephone.html, I had:\n```javascript\nconst audio = new Audio(API_BASE + deanMsg.audioFile);\n```\n\nWhere `API_BASE` is empty string `''` for relative URLs. This means:\n- On Mac: it tries `http://localhost:8790/audio/reply_xxx.mp3` ✓\n\n\n- On iPhone via Tailscale: it tries `https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/audio/reply_xxx.mp3` ✓\n\nSo the relative URL approach handles both the Mac and iPhone contexts correctly.\n\nNow I'm checking the last Dean log to see what's been happening recently.","thinkingSignature":"e301b7c49579d24974b41c1bbe9247f8383ff48ed0df62929696045020b46c56"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lbtviem9cbsi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -5 ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-dean.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":499,"output":277,"cacheRead":100160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100936,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777675999545,"responseId":"064461df4ff690745e7b5e4d6f444814"}}
