{"type":"message","id":"230652ee","parentId":"51f3b656","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:33:35.991Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is frustrated. The server keeps dying. Let me get to the bottom of this.\n\nThe issue is that server.js, dean.js, and the proxy keep dying. This is a fundamental infrastructure problem. Let me figure out why.\n\nKey issues:\n1. server.js crashes with EADDRINUSE when trying to restart\n2. The proxy dies\n3. dean.js dies\n\nI think the problem is that I'm not properly managing these processes. They keep dying and I'm restarting them manually. Let me create a proper launcher script that keeps them running.\n\nBut first, let me understand WHY they keep dying.\n","thinkingSignature":"9a0eb8894756aa6daacc66a9ab7532e77cca5a2ccfd99b9be2ad7604fabffe0b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_90k06psk33n8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check why processes are dying - look at error logs\necho \"=== Server errors ===\"\ngrep -i \"error\\|fatal\\|crash\" ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone.log 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Dean errors ===\"  \ngrep -i \"error\\|fatal\\|crash\" ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone-dean.log 2>/dev/null | tail -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Recent server log ===\"\ntail -20 ~/.openclaw/logs/telephone.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107667,"output":266,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108125,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777681990505,"responseId":"06447947399bd6bd0e10918494f902de"}}
