{"type":"message","id":"cbce7540","parentId":"a2145a8f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:35:37.438Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is emoji characters in the AI response causing the `say` command to fail. When I send \"Hey Bobby! 🤖🦞 What's up?\" to the `say` command, it fails because of the emoji characters in the string.\n\nThe fix is in the TTS cleanup - I need to also remove emoji characters before passing to `say`. Let me fix dean.js to properly strip all emoji before the say command.\n\nCurrent dean.js has:\n```javascript\nconst clean = text.replace(/[\"\\\\]/g, '').replace(/[🤖🦞🔥💀😂❤️👍✨📺🎉💡]/g, '').replace(/\\n+/g, ' ').replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n```\n\nBut it's missing other emoji and the weird character \"\" suggests there's a character encoding issue. I should use a broader emoji removal pattern.\n","thinkingSignature":"0e6fdd3982753eb92eabfe802dc59479e985354c8a05e2452d1ccc982fc08b09"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound it. The AI responses contain emoji (like 🤖🦞) that break the `say` command. Let me fix the TTS to strip ALL emoji properly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kv624n2hvnl9_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Telephone — Dean Response Generator\n * Uses OpenClaw's /v1/chat/completions endpoint to route to the main \"Dean\" session\n */\n\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\n\nconst PORT_DEAN = 8791;\nconst GATEWAY_PORT = 18789;\nconst STATE_FILE = path.join(__dirname, '.last_check');\nconst MESSAGES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'messages.json');\nconst AUDIO_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'audio');\n\n// Emoji regex - matches all emoji characters\nconst EMOJI_REGEX = /[\\u{1F300}-\\u{1F9FF}]|[\\u{2600}-\\u{26FF}]|[\\u{2700}-\\u{27BF}]|[\\u{1F600}-\\u{1F64F}]|[\\u{1F680}-\\u{1F6FF}]|[\\u{1F1E0}-\\u{1F1FF}]|[\\u{2300}-\\u{23FF}]|[\\u{2190}-\\u{21FF}]|[\\u{2640}-\\u